## I. One object, one relation, one equation, one dichotomy

**Unifying principle.**
$$\boxed{\;\text{Every }E_1\text{-chiral algebra on }\overline M_{g,n}\text{ with translation-invariant point-local OPE, semisimple }L_0\text{, principal-subregular DS-nilpotent data factors under }\mathrm{av}\text{ into }\mathsf G/\mathsf L/\mathsf C/\mathsf M/\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}/\mathsf B\text{ with }\kappa+\kappa^!\in\{0,8,13,250/3,98/3\}.\;}$$

**Object.** $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)=T^c(s^{-1}\bar A)$ on $\overline M_{g,n}$; ordered primitive, $B^{\mathrm{sym}}$ derived quotient under $\mathrm{av}$.

**Relation.** Arnold $\eta_{ij}\wedge\eta_{jk}+\eta_{jk}\wedge\eta_{ki}+\eta_{ki}\wedge\eta_{ij}=0$ on $\mathrm{Conf}_n$; $\mathbb P^1$ adjoin $\sum_{j\ne i}\bar\eta_{ij}=0$; $\Sigma_g$ Totaro–Kriz.

**Equation.** $D\Theta_A+\tfrac12[\Theta_A,\Theta_A]=0$.

**Dichotomy (six-row spine).** Canonical witnesses: $\mathcal H_k$, $V_k(\mathfrak g)$, $\beta\gamma_\lambda$, $\mathrm{Vir}_c$, $\mathrm{BP}_k=\mathcal W(\widehat{\mathfrak{sl}}_3,f_{\mathrm{min}})$, $\mathbf H_{\Delta_5}$. $\mathsf M/\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$ distinction: $\mathsf M$ = principal nilpotent (bosonic $\mathcal W_N$); $\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$ = subregular/minimal (BP, bosonic+fermionic $G^\pm$ half-integer weight). BP cocycle does not cohomologise into $\mathrm{Vir}_c$. Ceiling $\kappa+\kappa^!=8$ on $\mathsf B$ via Bruinier–Heegner.

**Three-lens square.**
$$\begin{array}{ccc}
\mathrm{CY}_d^{\mathrm{cat}}&\xrightarrow{\;\Phi^{\mathrm{FA}}_d\;}&\mathrm{Fact}^{\mathrm{hol}}_{E_d}(X)\\
\big\downarrow\,{\scriptstyle\mathrm{Shad}_\bullet}&&\big\downarrow\,{\scriptstyle\mathrm{Sp}^{\mathrm{ch}}_{\Sigma_{d-1},C}}\\
\mathrm{Alg}_{E_1^{\mathrm{ch}}}(C)&\xleftarrow[\;\Omega^{\mathrm{ch}}_C\;]{B^{\mathrm{ch}}_C}&\mathrm{CoAlg}^{\mathrm{fact}}_{E_1^{\mathrm{ch}}}(C)
\end{array}$$
Commuting up to $\Omega^{\mathrm{ch}}_C\circ B^{\mathrm{ch}}_C\Rightarrow\mathrm{id}$ on Koszul locus. Vol I: bottom row; Vol II: right leg; Vol III: top row + right leg.

