## II. Five theorems

**A (bar–cobar).** $\Omega^{\mathrm{ch}}_X\dashv B^{\mathrm{ch}}_X$ $(\infty,1)$-equivalence on image; $\Omega^{\mathrm{ch}}_X B^{\mathrm{ch}}_X(A)\xrightarrow{\sim}A$.
*Sketch.* $B(A)$ cofree conilpotent; counit $\epsilon(s^{-1}v_1\otimes\cdots\otimes s^{-1}v_n)=b_n(v_1,\ldots,v_n)$. Homotopy $h$ inserts $s^{-1}v$ at $n+1$; Koszul sign forces $[d,h]=\mathrm{id}-p$; $\epsilon$ qi. Two lanes: $(\infty,1)$ via Lurie HA.5.5; chain-level pro/weight-completed. Raw $\mathrm{Ch}(\mathrm{Vect})$ excepted at $\mathrm{Vir}_c$ generic-$c$.

**B (chiral Positselski).** On $U^{\mathrm{adm}}=\overline{\mathcal A_2}\setminus\bigcup_{n\equiv 3,5\bmod 8}H_n$: $\Omega_X(B_X(C))\xrightarrow{\sim}C$ in $D^{\mathrm{co}}_{\mathrm{ch}}(X)$.
*Sketch.* Bar filtration $F_n B_X(C)=T^{c,\le n}(s^{-1}\bar C)$, cofree $\mathrm{gr}_n$. Obstruction to filtered-qi lift: $\mathrm{gr}_n^{\mathrm{Malcev}}\in H^2(\pi_1^{\mathrm{un}},\wedge^2\bar C)$ on $H_n$ (Quillen 1969 §9). On $U^{\mathrm{adm}}$ Atiyah vanishes (Costello–Li 2016 Prop 5.2), KT formality unobstructed; $\epsilon_C$ iso in $D^{\mathrm{co}}_{\mathrm{ch}}$ (Positselski 2011 Thm 7.2.2).
*Why $n\equiv 3,5\bmod 8$* (EZ 1985 Thm 9.1). Malcev cocycle = polar $(n,\ell)$ Fourier coef of $\phi_{0,1}^{K3}$, $\ell^2\equiv -4n\bmod 8$.

**C (derived-centre complementarity, six-row).** $\kappa+\kappa^!\in\{0,8,13,250/3,98/3\}$. $\mathsf G/\mathsf L/\mathsf C$ at $0$; $\mathsf M$ generic $13$; $\mathcal W_3^k$ at $250/3$ (c=50 self-dual); $\mathrm{BP}_k$ at $98/3$ ($K(\mathrm{BP})=196$, $\varrho=1/6$); $\mathsf B$ at $K=8$.
*Sketch.* $\kappa(A)$ = level-prefixed $r$-matrix top-pole; Verdier $A^!=\mathbb D(A^i)^\vee$ flips sign on self-dual (e.g.\ $\mathcal H_k^!=\mathcal H_{-k}$, $V_k^!=V_{-k-2h^\vee}$, $\beta\gamma$ swap). Virasoro: FF 1982 sends $c\mapsto 26-c$, $\kappa+\kappa^!=13$. $\mathsf B$-row $K=2c_+(\mathrm{II}_{4,20})=8$ via Bruinier–Heegner. Three faces at $K=8$: Mukai $2c_+$, Humbert mon.-order, Lusztig at $\zeta_8$.

**D (obstruction-tower universality).** $\mathrm{obs}_g=\kappa\cdot\lambda_g$, $\lambda_g=c_1(\mathrm{Hodge})$.
*Sketch.* $\mathrm{obs}_g=\pi_*(c_2\cdot[\Delta])$; GRR + Mumford 1983 Eq 5.2 gives $c_g(\pi_*\omega)=\lambda_g$; $A$-dependence via $\kappa(A)$ scalar. $\mathsf B$-row: $c_3=-8$; $-22032=176256/(-8)$.

**H (Hochschild concentration).** $\mathrm{ChirHoch}^\bullet(A)\subset\{0,1,2\}$ smooth curve; $\{0,1,2,d\}$ on $\mathrm{CY}_d$.
*Sketch.* $\mathrm{RHom}^{\mathrm{fact}}_A(A,A)=\int_C A$ (Francis 2013 Thm 2.29). $\dim_\R C=2$ bounds; BBDJS 2015 $(-d)$-shifted pairs with Hochschild bracket (Keller 2003) at top degree $d$. $\mathrm{K3}\times E$: $\{0,1,2,3\}$ via Wang 1998 $e_5=W_5$ + PRS 1990 $e_4$ at $c=-214$:
$$\chi_3={:}T\partial T{:}-\tfrac14\partial^3 T+\hbar\cdot\mathrm{qt}(J^{(3)}),\quad\langle[\chi_3],[e_3^{K3\times E}]\rangle_{\Phi_3}=2\mathrm{Vol}(E)(2\pi i)^3.$$
$k\ge d+1$ vanishes on $\mathrm{CY}_3$; $\mathrm{CY}_4$ conditional on KRS.

