## III-bis. Canonical order

$$\boxed{\;\mathsf G<\mathsf L<\mathsf C<\mathsf M<\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}<\mathsf B\;}$$

Lexicographic forcing triple $(\mathrm{stratum},r_{\max},\mathrm{DS\text{-}depth})$: stratum $\in\{0,1,2\}$ (Verdier-self-dual / FF-reflected $\mathcal W$ / Mukai-trace BKM ceiling $K^\kappa=8$); $r_{\max}\in\{2,3,4,\infty\}$ shadow-tower depth; DS-depth is the Stratum-1 tiebreaker (principal $<$ subregular) that distinguishes $\mathsf M<\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$ at their common $r_{\max}=\infty$. Scope-tightening (Beilinson r5-redux-B, Cycle 4): DS-depth is not globally monotone along the six-row spine — DS-depth values are $\{\text{no},\text{no},\text{no},\text{prin},\text{sub},\text{no}\}$ on $\mathsf G/\mathsf L/\mathsf C/\mathsf M/\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}/\mathsf B$; its role is strictly the Stratum-1 tiebreaker. Equivalently, a binary "contains half-integer-weight fermionic generator" invariant separates $\mathsf M$ (bosonic tower $(W_2,\ldots,W_N)$) from $\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$ (bosonic $(T,J)$ plus fermionic $G^\pm$), and DS-depth is the canonical structural refinement encoding the Jacobson--Morozov nilpotent-orbit origin. Either presentation gives lex-injective total order; the third component is load-bearing only on Stratum 1.

Stratum 0: $\mathsf G<\mathsf L<\mathsf C$ via $r_{\max}=2,3,4$ Arnold-residue filtration ($\mathcal H$ closes $b_2$ at $n=2$; $V_k(\mathfrak g)$ three-point Arnold chain; $\beta\gamma$ four-point Totaro-Kriz). Stratum 1: $\mathsf M<\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$ via principal $f_\theta$ vs subregular $f_{\min}$ DS-depth; BP $G^\pm$ fermionic cocycle non-trivial, does not cohomologise into $\mathcal W_N$ (Bershadsky 1991 + Arakawa 2005). Stratum 2: $\mathsf B$ terminal via $\hbar^2 K=-1$ on Calabi-Yau-BKM target, three routes at $K=8$ (Mukai $2c_+(\mathrm{II}_{4,20})$; Humbert monodromy on $H_1$; Lusztig $\ell=8$ in $\mathfrak u_{\zeta_8}$).

Three invariants independent: Verdier on $(A,A^!)$; Arnold-residue pole on $\mathrm{Conf}_n(C)$; Jacobson-Morozov on $\mathcal N(\mathfrak g)$. Numerical $\kappa+\kappa^!\in\{0,0,0,13,250/3,98/3,8\}$ does NOT force order ($\mathsf B$ at 8 would precede $\mathsf M$ at 13). Five transitions: $\mathsf G\to\mathsf L\to\mathsf C$ $r_{\max}$-increments at self-duality; $\mathsf C\to\mathsf M$ stratum 0→1 FF-reflection via $c\mapsto 26-c$; $\mathsf M\to\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$ DS-descent principal→subregular; $\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}\to\mathsf B$ stratum 1→2 Mukai-trace via Bruinier-Heegner. Terminal $\mathsf B$: $\mathrm{II}_{4,20}$ maximal, $\mathrm{Aut}^\circ(K3\times E)=E$ no $\mathbb G_m$; three-route does not repeat at higher rank without Serre-CM lift.

\ClaimStatusProvedHere: stratum labels; $r_{\max}$ inequalities; DS-depth $\mathsf M<\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$ (Bershadsky 1991 + Arakawa 2005); lexicographic injectivity. Terminal $\mathsf B$ three-route unconditional (Bruinier 2002 + Gritsenko 1999 + Lusztig 1990); Serre-CM lift \ClaimStatusConjectured.

