## XX. Theorem B closes bar-cobar into derived equivalence

Theorem A gives adjoint pair with counit weak-equivalence on Koszul locus. $D^{\mathrm{co}}_{\mathrm{ch}}(X)$ supplies differentials along Humbert-unipotent strata obstructing strict inverse. Theorem B forcing inverse: on $U^{\mathrm{adm}}$, $\Omega_X B_X(C)\xrightarrow{\sim}C$ isomorphism for every quasi-cofree $C$, realising bar-cobar as $(\infty,1)$-equivalence.

**Proof sketch.** Bar filtration $F_n B_X(C)=T^{c,\le n}(s^{-1}\bar C)$, cofree $\mathrm{gr}_n=\mathrm{Sym}^n[n]$; $\epsilon_C$ strict iso per graded piece. Malcev cocycle $\mathrm{gr}_n^{\mathrm{Malcev}}$ on Humbert $H_n$, non-zero exactly at $n\equiv 3,5\bmod 8$ (EZ 1985 + $\phi_{0,1}^{K3}$ polar). On $U^{\mathrm{adm}}$ Atiyah vanishes, Malcev cocycles vanish; $\epsilon_C$ qi of Bar-filtration towers; iso in $D^{\mathrm{co}}_{\mathrm{ch}}$ (Positselski 2011 Thm 7.2.2). Coderived localises stratum-wise, suffices without strict convergence.

Theorem B is *pivot*: $B\to A\to C\to\kappa+\kappa^!\to\kappa\lambda_g\to\{0,1,2\}$, unique arrow closing A-adjunction into derived equivalence. Without B: C/D/H have no canonical object. With B: five theorems are one theorem in five registers.

**Primary sources.** Positselski 2011 Mem AMS 212; EZ 1985 Thm 9.1; Chenevier 2014 Thm 2.12; BD 2004 §§3.3–3.4; Lurie HA §5.5; FG 2012.

