## XXVII. Drinfeld r4 — 6-row closure: landmark, not classification

The question: is the spine $\mathsf G/\mathsf L/\mathsf C/\mathsf M/\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}/\mathsf B$ with $K^\kappa\in\{0,8,13,250/3,98/3\}$ a closure theorem, or a landmark enumeration? Five cycles of Drinfeld attack resolve: **landmark enumeration on the principal-subregular-at-$\mathfrak{sl}_3$ stratum plus $\mathsf B$-row K3; the $K^\kappa$ spectrum opens to an unbounded dense-rational set outside that stratum.** Six-row spine closed on its scope and open past it; no seventh archetype is required, because the *archetype* classification (G/L/C/M/B) is exhaustive in the Trinity-$\varrho$-sense, while the *$K^\kappa$-value bucket* is open.

**Cycle 1 — DS-nilpotent exhaustion on $\mathfrak{sl}_n$.** Nilpotent orbits of $\mathfrak{sl}_n$ are partitions of $n$: trivial $\{0\}$; minimal $\mathbb O_{\min}=(2,1^{n-2})$; hook $(n-r,1^r)$ for $1\le r\le n-2$; rectangular $(k^{n/k})$ for $k\mid n$; subregular $(n-1,1)$; principal $(n)$. For each $f\in\mathbb O$, the DS reduction $\mathcal W^k(\mathfrak{sl}_n,f)$ has $c$ and Feigin-Frenkel dual $c^!$; the anomaly ratio $\varrho(f)=\kappa/c$ depends on the $\mathfrak{sl}_2$-type decomposition with respect to the $\mathfrak{sl}_2$-triple $(e,h,f)$. Principal $f_{\mathrm{prin}}$: $\varrho=\sum_{i=1}^{n-1} 1/(m_i+1)=H_n-1$. Subregular at $\mathfrak{sl}_3$ (BP): $\varrho=1/6$. Rectangular $(k^{n/k})$: $\varrho_{\mathrm{rect}}(k,n/k)=(n/k)(H_k-1)$ by Kac-Roan-Wakimoto 2003 Thm 6.1. Hook $(n-r,1^r)$: $\varrho_{\mathrm{hook}}$ interpolates principal and minimal via Arakawa 2015 Cor 7.2. Koszul conductor $K=c+c^!$ grows polynomially in $n$ with orbit-dependent coefficient. Products $K^\kappa=\varrho\cdot K$ rational at Koszul self-dual locus, generically distinct from the 6-row values. Hook $(3,1,1)$ at $n=5$: $K^\kappa$ neither $0,8,13,250/3$ nor $98/3$. **Conclusion C1.** DS-nilpotent hierarchy past $\mathfrak{sl}_3$ already gives infinitely many distinct $K^\kappa$ values. Six-row spine is not closed under $K^\kappa$-sum but closed under archetype-label G/L/C/M/B: every DS-reduced algebra with non-zero fermionic generators enters $\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$ (subregular/minimal, fermionic $G^\pm$); bosonic principal enters $\mathsf M$; no seventh type.

**Cycle 2 — exotic ambients.** (i) *Log-VOA $\mathcal W(p)$*: triplet algebra, $c=1-6(p-1)^2/p$; $L_0$ non-semisimple on modules but semisimple on $\mathcal W(p)$ itself. Adamovic-Milas 2008 Thm 4.1: $\mathcal W(p)\in\mathsf M$ via $T$-channel $r_{\max}^T=\infty$. $K^\kappa$ values generically distinct from 13 due to non-self-dual Feigin-Tipunin 2010 Prop 5.3 structure. Logarithmic phenomena on modules, not algebra archetype. (ii) *Topological VOA at critical level*: $\widehat{\mathfrak{g}}_{-h^\vee}$ has infinite centre Feigin-Frenkel 1992; $c=0$ kills anomaly but Sugawara fails so $T$ does not exist chirally. Koszul locus excluded (Arakawa 2017 Rem 4.9); no $K^\kappa$ defined. Boundary degeneration of $\mathsf L$, not a seventh archetype. (iii) *Vertex chiral DG-algebras with non-trivial BRST* (CG FA Vol 2 §5.3): Trinity gives $K^\kappa=-c_{\mathrm{ghost}}\cdot\varrho$. Every such algebra enters G/L/C/M/B by underlying bosonic reduction. **Conclusion C2.** No exotic-ambient seventh row.

**Cycle 3 — fracton-like chiral algebras (non-local OPE).** Fracton models (Vijay-Haah-Fu 2016 PRB; Pretko 2018) have non-local OPEs with support on codimension $\ge 1$ sub-manifolds. Hypothesis of the six-row classification is **translation-invariant point-local OPE**; fracton OPEs violate point-locality: $\phi(z_1)\phi(z_2)$ has support on a sub-variety in $z_1-z_2$ rather than pole structure at $\Delta$. Bar complex defined but Maurer-Cartan $\Theta_A$ fails to exist (residue at diagonal vanishes). **Conclusion C3.** Fracton algebras sit *outside the hypothesis*, not a seventh row — scope-exclusion parallel to class W wild-quiver Kronecker $K_m$ ($m\ge 3$) at `landscape_census.tex:569`. Both W and "F" (fracton) sit outside the classification domain.

**Cycle 4 — non-rational CFTs (irrational $c$, continuous spectrum).** (i) *Liouville* $c=1+6Q^2$: chiral half is $\mathrm{Vir}_c$ at irrational $c$; $c+c^!=26$, $K^\kappa=13$ exactly. Liouville sits inside $\mathsf M$. Continuous spectrum affects modules, not algebra. (ii) *Free boson at irrational radius*: $\mathcal H_1$ with $K^\kappa=0$ — inside $\mathsf G$ regardless of radius. (iii) *Irrational-$c$ $\mathcal W_N$*: $c$ irrational at irrational $k$; $K_c=4N^3-2N-2$ rational constant; $K^\kappa=(H_N-1)(4N^3-2N-2)$ rational, *independent of $k$*. Every $k$ in $\mathcal W_N$-family lands same $K^\kappa$. **Conclusion C4.** Irrationality of $c$ does not escape archetype; non-rational CFTs fit inside six-row spine.

**Cycle 5 — closure proof via OPE-pole-structure exhaustion.** An $E_1$-chiral algebra $A$ on $C$ with translation-invariant point-local OPE has OPE data $\{A_{ij}^k, r(z)\}$ with $r(z)=\sum_{n\ge 1} R_n/z^n$. Pole depth $r_{\max}=\sup\{n:R_n\ne 0\}$. On semisimple-$L_0$ locus, Jacobi forces $R_n$ to be $\mathfrak{sl}_2\times\mathfrak{sl}_2$-intertwiners from $L_0$-grading. Four exhaustive possibilities: (a) $r_{\max}=1$ Heisenberg central scalar — class $\mathsf G$; (b) $r_{\max}=2$, $R_2$ abelian-plus-Lie — class $\mathsf L$ KM Casimir+bracket; (c) $r_{\max}\in\{3,4\}$, $R_2\ne 0$ bosonic — class $\mathsf C$ $\beta\gamma$ contact-Weyl; (d) $r_{\max}=\infty$ unbounded, stress tensor $T$ strong generator — class $\mathsf M$ principal or $\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$ subregular. Exhausts semisimple-$L_0$ point-local stratum. $\mathsf B$-row adds lattice-parametric CoHA/Hall via two-stage $\Phi_d$ on K3 — cross-volume CY-enhancement, not OPE-pole archetype. **Conclusion C5.** On fixed $r_{\max}\in\{1,2,3,4,\infty\}$ strata plus $\mathsf B$-row K3 Mukai enhancement, six archetypes exhaust. No seventh $r_{\max}$-stratum: $r_{\max}\notin\{1,2\}$ with $R_1=R_2=0$ is either trivial (all $R_n=0$) or higher-depth; fractional $r_{\max}$ excluded by integer pole orders; no irrational $r_{\max}$. Archetype taxonomy G/L/C/M/B with $\mathsf M$ split principal/subregular on $\mathfrak{sl}_3$-DS is closed; $K^\kappa$-bucket $\{0,8,13,250/3,98/3\}$ is five-landmark witness; opens past $\mathfrak{sl}_3$.

**Net Drinfeld r4 verdict.** (a) *Archetype closure*: six-row spine closed on point-local translation-invariant semisimple-$L_0$ hypothesis plus $\mathsf B$-row K3 Mukai enhancement; proof by $r_{\max}$ pole-depth exhaustion. (b) *$K^\kappa$-value non-closure*: spectrum opens past five landmarks to unbounded dense-rational subset of $\mathbb R_+$ on $\mathcal W_{N\ge 4}^k(\mathfrak{sl}_n,f)$ family; explicit $K^\kappa(\mathcal W_4^{\mathrm{prin}})=533/2$, $K^\kappa(\mathcal W_5^{\mathrm{prin}})=9394/15$, $K^\kappa(\mathcal W_6^{\mathrm{prin}})=2465/2$ (Gelfand r3 + Opus Gelfand R4 N=8,9,10). (c) *Scope-exclusions outside hypothesis*: class W wild quiver, class F fracton non-local OPE, critical-level $\widehat{\mathfrak{g}}_{-h^\vee}$ Sugawara failure — *outside* classification domain, not additional rows. (d) *No seventh archetype*. Exotic ambients (log-VOA, topological VOA, BRST DG), fractons (excluded by hypothesis), non-rational CFTs (Liouville, irrational $\mathcal W$) reduce to existing archetypes or scope-exclude. Six-row spine is the correct taxonomy; $K^\kappa\in\{0,8,13,250/3,98/3\}$ is five-landmark witness with "landmark enumeration, not classification" labelling per Gelfand r3 on $\mathcal W_{N\ge 4}$ outside.

**Drinfeld r4 closure statement.** Every translation-invariant point-local $L_0$-semisimple $E_1$-chiral algebra on $\overline M_{g,n}$ admits pole depth $r_{\max}\in\{1,2,3,4,\infty\}$; the four finite strata $\{1,2,3,4\}$ are $\mathsf G,\mathsf L,\mathsf C$ respectively (with $r_{\max}=3,4$ collapsing onto $\mathsf C$ via $S_4\ne 0$ signature); the $r_{\max}=\infty$ stratum splits by DS-nilpotent data into $\mathsf M$ (principal, purely bosonic) and $\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$ (subregular or minimal, fermionic $G^\pm$-generators present); the $\mathsf B$-row is the cross-volume $\Phi_d$-Mukai enhancement on K3 at $K^\kappa=8$. Six rows exhaust; $K^\kappa$ spectrum outside $\{0,8,13,250/3,98/3\}$ populates the $\mathsf M$-row densely on $\mathcal W_{N\ge 4}$ and the $\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$-row densely on hook-type at $n\ge 5$.

**References (r4).** Fateev-Lukyanov 1988 Int J Mod Phys A 3 on $c(\mathcal W_N)$; Arakawa 2015 Duke 165 Thm 4.5 hook-type; Creutzig-Linshaw 2019 JEMS 21 hook-OPE; Kac-Roan-Wakimoto 2003 Comm Math Phys 241 Thm 6.1 DS-rectangular $\varrho$; Adamovic-Milas 2008 IMRN on $\mathcal W(p)$; Feigin-Frenkel 1992 PLB critical-level centre; Kronecker/wild quiver per `landscape_census.tex:569`; Vijay-Haah-Fu 2016 PRB 94 fracton hypothesis scope; Teschner 2001 Liouville; Bouwknegt-Schoutens 1993 PRep $\mathcal W$-algebra central-charge sums; Bala-Carter 1976 for nilpotent orbit classification.

