Baker-Heegner-Stark: 9 imaginary quadratic fields of class number 1, $n\in\{1,2,3,7,11,19,43,67,163\}$, fundamental discriminants $d_K\in\{-3,-4,-7,-8,-11,-19,-43,-67,-163\}$. Per $d_K$: singular K3 $X_{d_K}$ at $\rho=20$, transcendental lattice $T(X_{d_K})$ the unique positive-definite binary form of discriminant $|d_K|$ (Shioda-Mitani 1974 Thm 4.3). Shioda-Inose cover $X_{d_K}\to A_{d_K}=E_{\tau_{d_K}}\times E_{\tau_{d_K}}$, $j(\tau_{d_K})\in\Z$ class-number-1 (Morrison 1984 Invent.\ 75 Thm 6.3). Kuga-Satake $A^{\mathrm{KS}}_{d_K}\sim E_{\tau_{d_K}}^{\otimes 4}$ CM abelian 4-fold (Deligne 1972 Invent.\ 15 §6).

