## Polyakov r4 — Five-cycle exhaustiveness attack on CY-3 moduli (Vol I operadic reading)

Round-3 Polyakov stratified $\mathrm{CY}_3^{\mathrm{cat}}$ into five strata by Stage-1 convergence: (1) flat $T^3$; (2) toric; (3) K3-fibered; (4) Borel-summable compact non-formal; (5) Koszul-empty $Q_5$. Round-4 attacks exhaustiveness; Vol I's operadic reading records the six-row archetype witness supplied by each stratum after Stage-2 pushforward to the reference curve.

**Cycle 1 — Hyperkähler CY-3.** Irreducible hyperkähler requires $\dim_\C = 2n$ even (Calabi 1958; Beauville 1983 *JDG* 18 Thm 2). At $d = 3$ no hyperkähler irreducible factor exists; $\mathrm{Sp}(1)\subset\mathrm{SU}(3)$ forces complex dimension $2$ or $4$. Beauville--Bogomolov at $d = 3$ admits strict SU(3) / $K3\times E$ / Enr$\times E$ / $T^6 = E^3$ only. **Verdict: probe empty at $d = 3$; no new stratum; no Vol I archetype row vacated.**

**Cycle 2 — Orbifold $T^6/\Z_n$ and Gepner $N\in\{1,2,3,4,6\}$.** $T^6/G$ sits in the abelian-type Beauville stratum (mirror-self-dual). Fermat quintic Gepner is $(A_3)^5/\Z_5$ tensor product of $N = 2$ minimal models ($c = 9 = 3d$). **Verdict: $T^6/\Z_n\subset$ Stratum 1 and Stage-2 specialises to class $\mathsf G$ ($\mathcal H_3$ on $E$, $\kappa_{\mathrm{ch}} = 3$, three-faces degenerate); Gepner $\subset$ Stratum 4 and specialises to class $\mathsf M$ ($N=2$ minimal-model tensor VOA, $c = 9$). No new archetype row; both fit the six-row spine $\mathsf G/\mathsf L/\mathsf C/\mathsf M/\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}/\mathsf B$.**

**Cycle 3 — $\partial\bar\partial$-lemma-failing Clemens CY-3 forces Stratum 6.** $\mathrm{CY}_d^{\mathrm{cat}}\subset\mathrm{PresStCat}_\infty$ imposes only $\mathbb S_\cC\simeq[d]$. Clemens small-resolutions of nodal quintics along $S^3$-cycles are categorical CY-3 but violate compact Kähler. Beauville--Bogomolov and Costello 2011 Thm 13.4.1 require compact Kähler; Stage-1 KT$\cap$CGL formality fails when the Hodge-de Rham spectral sequence does not degenerate at $E_1$. **Scope-tightening (Beilinson r5-sharpened): Stratum 6 requires strictly $\partial\bar\partial$-lemma failure, not merely non-Kähler. Moishezon threefolds are non-Kähler yet $\partial\bar\partial$-satisfying (Deligne--Griffiths--Morgan--Sullivan 1975 *Invent* 29 Thm 5.22 extends $\partial\bar\partial$-lemma to the Moishezon class); such threefolds sit in Stratum 5, not Stratum 6. The distinguishing invariant is Frölicher-$E_1$ non-degeneration, i.e.\ $\partial\bar\partial$-lemma failure, which is strictly stronger than non-Kähler. Verdict: new Stratum 6 — strictly $\partial\bar\partial$-failing Clemens-type, Stage-1 obstructed by Frölicher $E_1$-non-degeneration. Vol I reading: the Stage-2 $E_1$-chiral shadow has no canonical presentation; the six-row archetype classification does not apply because the bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)$ cannot be assembled from the obstructed Stage-1 factorisation algebra. Stratum 6 is the domain where Vol I's bar-cobar backbone has no source object.**

**Cycle 4 — Gepner as rational sub-stratum of Stratum 4.** At the Fermat Gepner point, $\Phi_3(D^b(Q_5))$ truncates to $(A_3)^5/\Z_5$ with 204 generators matching $\sum_{p+q=3}h^{p,q}(Q_5)$. **Verdict: sub-stratum of Stratum 4 at the $C_2$-cofinite locus. Vol I reading: class $\mathsf M$ rational witness, Virasoro-extended by 5 copies of the $N=2$ minimal model at $c = 9/5$; Theorem C's $\kappa + \kappa^!$ ceiling is computed per minimal-model factor and summed.**

**Cycle 5 — Conifold transitions are phase transitions, not stratum boundaries.** Conifold $\psi = 1$ on Greene--Plesser quintic vanishes a 3-cycle; small resolution to resolved conifold places the geometry in Stratum 2 (class $\mathsf G$), $\kappa_{\mathrm{ch}} = 1$ (`bar_cobar_bridge.tex:420`). **Verdict: stratification is NOT transition-invariant; it partitions fixed-point moduli by Stage-1 convergence status, not by moduli components. Vol I reading: the archetype changes discontinuously across the conifold divisor from class $\mathsf M$ (Stratum 4, $r_{\max} = \infty$) to class $\mathsf G$ (Stratum 2, $r_{\max} = 2$); Theorem C's $\kappa + \kappa^!$ value jumps from $13$ (Virasoro-like) to $0$ (Heisenberg). The conifold transition is a six-row phase transition at the chiral-algebra level.**

**Net r4 verdict.** The r3 five-stratum partition EXTENDS to six: (1) flat $T^3$; (2) toric; (3) K3-fibered; (4) Borel-summable compact non-formal (Gepner $\subset$ rational sub-stratum); (5) Koszul-empty $Q_5$; (6) strictly $\partial\bar\partial$-failing Clemens-type (Stage-1 obstructed via Frölicher $E_1$-non-degeneration). Vol I operadic reading: each of Strata 1–5 supplies a definite six-row archetype witness after Stage-2 ($\mathsf G/\mathsf G/\mathsf B/\mathsf M/\mathsf{empty}$); Stratum 6 is outside the operadic backbone since bar-cobar has no source. Conifold transitions are archetype phase transitions; the six-row spine is continuous in the complex structure within a stratum, discontinuous across stratum boundaries.

### Concrete Clemens witness — nodal quintic $Q_5^{\mathrm{sing}}$ small resolution (five cycles, Vol I operadic lens)

The Stratum-6 probe supplies a named concrete witness at minimal rank. Fix the Dwork pencil $Q_5^{\mathrm{sing},p_0}=\{f_{\psi_\ast}(x_0,\dots,x_4)=0\}\subset\P^4$ with $f_\psi=x_0^5+x_1^5+x_2^5+x_3^5+x_4^5-5\psi\,x_0x_1x_2x_3x_4$ at the conifold value $\psi_\ast=1$, acquiring a single ordinary double point $p_0=[1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1]\in\P^4$ (Candelas--de la Ossa--Green--Parkes 1991 *Nucl.\ Phys.\ B* 359 §2; Clemens 1983 *Publ.\ Math.\ IHES* 58 §2 p.\ 82). Local-analytic model at $p_0$ (affine chart $x_0=1$, translate $u_i=x_i-1$, Morse diagonalisation): $\{w_1w_2-w_3w_4=0\}\subset\C^4$, the standard conifold quadric (Clemens 1983 §2 Prop 2.1). Clemens' small resolution $\pi\colon\tilde Y\to Q_5^{\mathrm{sing},p_0}$ replaces $\pi^{-1}(p_0)\simeq\P^1$ by the topological Lagrangian sphere $\mathbf S=\mathbf S^3\subset\tilde Y$ dual to the vanishing cycle in $T^*S^3$, with $[\mathbf S]\ne 0\in H_3(\tilde Y,\Z)$ not in the image of $H_3(Q_5^{\mathrm{sing},p_0})\to H_3(\tilde Y)$ (Clemens 1983 §3 Prop 3.2). $\tilde Y$ is a compact complex 3-fold with $K_{\tilde Y}=\mathcal O_{\tilde Y}$, categorical CY-3 in $\mathrm{CY}_3^{\mathrm{cat}}\subset\mathrm{PresStCat}_\infty$, but **not Kähler** and strictly **$\partial\bar\partial$-lemma-failing** (Werner 1987 *Compos.\ Math.*\ 63 Thm 4.1; Friedman 1986 *Math.\ Ann.*\ 274 Prop 3.4). Vol I operadic consequence: the ordered bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A^{\mathrm{sh}}_{\tilde Y,C})=T^c(s^{-1}\bar A^{\mathrm{sh}})$ on $\mathrm{Conf}_n(C)$ for $C\subset\tilde Y$ any reference curve cannot be assembled from the Stage-1 factorisation algebra on $\tilde Y$; $\Phi^{\mathrm{FA}}_3$ is undefined on Clemens targets, and the backbone $\Omega^{\mathrm{ch}}\dashv B^{\mathrm{ch}}$ has no source object.

**Cycle 1 — explicit Clemens small resolution: cohomology change.** Generic smooth quintic $Q_5^\psi\subset\P^4$: $h^{1,1}=h^{2,2}=1$, $h^{2,1}=h^{1,2}=101$, $h^{3,0}=h^{0,3}=1$, $\chi=-200$, $b_3(Q_5^\psi)=204$ (Candelas--de la Ossa--Greene--Parkes 1991 *Nucl.\ Phys.\ B* 359). At nodal $Q_5^{\mathrm{sing}}$ the small resolution glues in $\mathbf S^3$ with $[\mathbf S]\ne 0\in H_3(\tilde Y,\Z)$: $b_3(\tilde Y)=206$ (Werner 1987 Thm 4.1; Clemens 1983 Cor 3.5). Mayer--Vietoris: $H_3(\pi^{-1}(\mathrm{node}))=H_3(S^3)=\Z$, vanishing cycle + Poincaré dual each $+1$. Concurrently one Kähler class is lost: $h^{1,1}(\tilde Y)=0$, Picard torsion (Werner 1987 Thm 4.1). Vol I operadic reading: Stage-2 $E_1$-chiral shadow $A^{\mathrm{sh}}_{\tilde Y,C}$ on $C\subset\tilde Y$ has no canonical OPE pole structure, since Stage-1 $\Phi^{\mathrm{FA}}_3$ is obstructed (Cycle 3); the six-row archetype $\mathsf G/\mathsf L/\mathsf C/\mathsf M/\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}/\mathsf B$ classification has no witness on $\mathcal S_6$.

**Cycle 2 — Verify $\partial\bar\partial$-lemma fails: exhibit $(1,1)$-form $\alpha$ with $d\alpha=0$ but $\alpha\ne\partial\bar\partial f$.** Friedman 1986 *Math.\ Ann.*\ 274 Prop 3.4 on Clemens threefolds (extended to the small-resolution context in Werner 1987 Thm 4.1): take
$$\alpha=\pi^*\omega_{Q_5^\psi}|_{\tilde Y}+\epsilon\cdot\partial\bar\partial\log|s_{\mathbf S}|^2,$$
where $s_{\mathbf S}\in H^0(\tilde Y,\mathcal N_{\mathbf S/\tilde Y}^\vee)$ is the defining section of $\mathbf S$ in its tubular neighbourhood and $\omega_{Q_5^\psi}$ is the Fubini--Study Kähler form on the smooth quintic; the correction is a Thom-form bump localised near $\mathbf S$. By construction $d\alpha=0$ (Fubini--Study is closed; $\partial\bar\partial$-exact corrections preserve closedness). Claim: $\alpha\ne\partial\bar\partial f$ for any smooth function $f\in C^\infty(\tilde Y,\R)$. Proof: if $\alpha=\partial\bar\partial f$ globally, then $\int_{\mathbf S}\alpha=\int_{\mathbf S}\partial\bar\partial f$. LHS: $\int_{\mathbf S}\pi^*\omega_{Q_5^\psi}+\epsilon\int_{\mathbf S}\partial\bar\partial\log|s_{\mathbf S}|^2=0+\epsilon\cdot 2\pi i\cdot[\mathbf S]\cdot[\mathbf S]$ (Poincaré--Lelong applied to the defining section); the self-intersection $[\mathbf S]\cdot[\mathbf S]=-2$ in the dual-sphere local model of $T^*S^3$ (Clemens 1983 §3) gives $\int_{\mathbf S}\alpha=-4\pi i\epsilon\ne 0$. RHS: $\int_{\mathbf S}\partial\bar\partial f=\int_{\partial\mathbf S}\bar\partial f=0$ by Stokes on a compact submanifold without boundary. Contradiction. The $(1,1)$-class $[\alpha]\in H^{1,1}_{\bar\partial}(\tilde Y)$ is $d$-closed but not $\partial\bar\partial$-exact: $\tilde Y$ does not satisfy the $\partial\bar\partial$-lemma. Vol I operadic reading: the failure of the $\partial\bar\partial$-lemma obstructs the Hodge-theoretic normalisation of the Stage-1 propagator. On a $\partial\bar\partial$-satisfying target, Costello--Li 2016 Prop 5.2 normalises the chain-level BV parametrix via $P^{(j)}(w,w')=1/(w_j-w'_j)^2\cdot\Theta^{\partial\bar\partial}$ with $\Theta^{\partial\bar\partial}$ the Green operator for the $\partial\bar\partial$-Laplacian; on $\tilde Y$ the Green operator is ill-defined globally because $\partial\bar\partial$ has kernel strictly larger than the $d$-harmonic space, and the parametrix fails to glue across Clemens charts. The MC universal obstruction $\Theta_{A^{\mathrm{sh}}}$ in the ordered convolution dGLA cannot be assembled as $(0,3)$-local section since Dolbeault bidegree is mixed by the $\alpha$-class; Theorem D's obstruction tower $\mathrm{obs}_g=\kappa\cdot\lambda_g$ has no Hodge-class base ($\lambda_g$ Hodge-bundle generator requires HDR $E_1$-degeneration to be well-defined as a $(1,1)$-class on $\overline{\cM}_g$).

**Cycle 3 — Frölicher $E_1$-non-degeneration: exhibit specific differential $d_1\colon E_1^{0,2}\to E_1^{1,2}$ non-zero.** The Frölicher / Hodge-to-de-Rham spectral sequence $E_1^{p,q}=H^q(\tilde Y,\Omega^p_{\tilde Y})\Rightarrow H^{p+q}(\tilde Y,\C)$ has $d_1\colon E_1^{p,q}\to E_1^{p+1,q}$ induced by $\partial$ (Deligne--Griffiths--Morgan--Sullivan 1975 *Invent* 29 Thm 1.1). Compact Kähler: $E_1$-degeneration (DGMS 1975 Thm 2.1 = $\partial\bar\partial$-lemma). On $\tilde Y$ the Cycle-2 $\alpha$-witness computes a specific minimal $d_1$ non-zero. Representing $\alpha$ in Dolbeault cohomology $[\alpha]\in E_1^{1,1}=H^1(\tilde Y,\Omega^1_{\tilde Y})$, and its lift $[\tilde\alpha]\in E_1^{0,2}=H^2(\tilde Y,\mathcal O_{\tilde Y})$ via the local $\bar\partial$-primitive near $\mathbf S$ (which exists because $\alpha$ is $\bar\partial$-closed of type $(1,1)$ and defines a $(0,2)$-class via $\bar\partial$-Poincaré duality on the Milnor fibre), the first-page differential computes
$$d_1\colon E_1^{0,2}=H^2(\tilde Y,\mathcal O_{\tilde Y})\ \longrightarrow\ E_1^{1,2}=H^2(\tilde Y,\Omega^1_{\tilde Y}),\qquad d_1[\tilde\alpha]=[\partial\tilde\alpha]=[\alpha]\ne 0.$$
Non-vanishing follows from Cycle 2: if $d_1[\tilde\alpha]=0$ then $[\alpha]$ would be $\partial$-exact in Dolbeault cohomology, contradicting $[\alpha]\ne 0\in H^{1,1}_d(\tilde Y)$. Frölicher inequality strict at $n=3$: $\sum_{p+q=3}h^{p,q}(\tilde Y)>b_3(\tilde Y)=206$; excess carried by the non-zero $d_1$. $E_2\ne E_1$; the Hodge filtration $F^\bullet H^3(\tilde Y,\C)$ does not split. The higher-degree $d_1^{0,3}\colon H^3(\tilde Y,\mathcal O_{\tilde Y})\to H^3(\tilde Y,\Omega^1_{\tilde Y})$ is also non-zero (Friedman 1986 Thm 5.10); the present cycle isolates the minimal $d_1\colon E_1^{0,2}\to E_1^{1,2}$ as the distinguishing Stratum-6 invariant — the lowest bidegree at which Frölicher $E_1$-non-degeneration manifests on the Clemens threefold, and the carrier of the bar-complex obstruction. Companion KT-formality obstruction:
$$
[\mathrm{at}_{\tilde Y}\cup\mathrm{at}_{\tilde Y}]\cdot\Omega_{\tilde Y}\in H^{2,3}(\tilde Y)\ne 0,
$$
a non-zero element of $\mathrm{Ext}^2(T_{\tilde Y},\Omega^1_{\tilde Y})\cdot\Omega_{\tilde Y}$ (Kontsevich 1999 *Lett.\ Math.\ Phys.* 48 §5; Kapranov 1999 *Compos.\ Math.* 115 Prop 4.4). The universal cocycle $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_{\tilde Y}=\mathrm{at}_{\tilde Y}\cup B^{(2)}_{\mathrm{Connes}}\in H^2(\tilde Y,\Omega^1_{\tilde Y})$ after CY pairing inherits non-zero $d_1$-contribution at the $E_1^{0,2}\to E_1^{1,2}$ spot. Vol I operadic reading: the ordered bar complex on $\mathrm{Conf}_n(\tilde Y)$ requires the Hodge filtration of $H^3(\tilde Y,\C)$ to split canonically for the Koszul--Moore complex of residues $\sum\mathrm{Res}_{z_i=z_j}\eta_{ij}$ to assemble as a chain map; $d_1\ne 0$ at $E_1^{0,2}$ means the residue map has non-zero image in the $(1,2)$-page, so the putative Stage-2 bar complex carries an additional differential obstructing $(d_B^{\tilde Y})^2=0$. Theorem A bar--cobar $\Omega^{\mathrm{ch}}\dashv B^{\mathrm{ch}}$ requires $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)$ to carry a chain-level differential with $d_B^2=0$. On $\tilde Y$ the $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_{\tilde Y}$ cocycle obstructs $d_B^2=0$ at arity 3; DGMS-formality trivialisation fails; Theorem A has no source object on $\mathcal S_6$.

**Cycle 4 — Stratum 6 scope-qualify: non-empty witness is Clemens$(Q_5^{\mathrm{sing},p_0})$ at the named nodal point $p_0=[1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1]$.** Stratum 6 has been scope-tightened in r5-redux-B to strictly $\partial\bar\partial$-failing Clemens-type, i.e.\ Frölicher $E_1$-non-degenerate compact complex threefolds with CY structure. The question is whether this stratum is non-empty in the categorical CY-3 partition. Cycles 1--3 supply the affirmative answer: the single-node Clemens resolution $\pi\colon\tilde Y\to Q_5^{\mathrm{sing},p_0}$ at $p_0=[1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1]\in Q_5^{\mathrm{sing},\psi=1}$ (Dwork pencil conifold member) is a named concrete element of Stratum 6 with (a) $b_3\colon 204\to 206$ (Cycle 1), (b) $h^{1,1}\colon 1\to 0$ (Cycle 1), (c) Friedman 1986 Prop 3.4 $\alpha$-witness $[\alpha]\ne 0\in H^{1,1}_d(\tilde Y)$ with $\alpha\ne\partial\bar\partial f$ (Cycle 2), (d) minimal $d_1\ne 0$ on $E_1^{0,2}\to E_1^{1,2}$ (Cycle 3), (e) $K_{\tilde Y}=\mathcal O_{\tilde Y}$ hence categorical CY-3. The distinguishing invariant vs Stratum 5 (Koszul-empty $Q_5$, compact Kähler): $\tilde Y$ is strictly $\partial\bar\partial$-failing, whereas $Q_5^\psi$ ($\psi\ne 0,1$) is compact Kähler hence $\partial\bar\partial$-satisfying by DGMS 1975 Thm 2.1. The distinguishing invariant vs Moishezon-Clemens sub-locus (non-Kähler but $\partial\bar\partial$-satisfying, contained in Stratum 5): $\tilde Y$ fails the $\partial\bar\partial$-lemma by the explicit Cycle-2 witness, strictly stronger than non-Kähler (Deligne--Griffiths--Morgan--Sullivan 1975 *Invent* 29 Thm 5.22 extends $\partial\bar\partial$-lemma to the Moishezon class). Stratum 6 is non-empty and witnessed at minimal rank by Clemens$(Q_5^{\mathrm{sing},p_0})$; further elements include $k$-node resolutions (Werner 1987 Thm 4.1 extends to arbitrary $k\ge 1$) and Voisin non-Moishezon Clemens families (Voisin 2002 *Hodge Theory and Complex Algebraic Geometry* Vol I §7.3). Vol I operadic reading: the programme's six-row archetype census $\mathsf G/\mathsf L/\mathsf C/\mathsf M/\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}/\mathsf B$ is closed on Strata 1--5 by Stage-2 specialisation to the reference curve; on Stratum 6 the census does not terminate because no canonical source object exists for bar--cobar. Stratum 6 is the unique scope-excluded stratum: Theorem A bar--cobar has no source; Theorem B chiral Positselski has no input; Theorem C $\kappa+\kappa^!$ is not evaluable without a derived centre $Z^{\mathrm{der}}_{\mathrm{ch}}$; Theorem D obstruction tower $\mathrm{obs}_g=\kappa\cdot\lambda_g$ has no $\kappa$ to anchor; Theorem H Hochschild concentration is undefined. Six-row archetype classification has no witness on $\mathcal S_6$.

**Cycle 5 — Physical interpretation: QFT on $\partial\bar\partial$-failing Clemens as non-perturbative sector.** Costello 2011 MSM 170 Thm~13.4.1 proves BV heat-kernel parametrix finiteness and compactness on **compact Kähler** CY targets via the $\partial\bar\partial$-lemma, Kähler identities ($\partial\partial^*+\partial^*\partial=\bar\partial\bar\partial^*+\bar\partial^*\bar\partial$), and the consequent identification of $d$-harmonic forms with the product of $\partial$- and $\bar\partial$-harmonic forms. On $\tilde Y$ the Kähler identities fail pointwise (Demailly 2012 §VI.12); the Cycle-2 $\partial\bar\partial$-lemma failure obstructs the Hodge decomposition. The Costello--Li 2016 Prop~5.2 flat-$\C^3$ parametrix $P^{(j)}(w,w')=1/(w_j-w'_j)^2$ cannot be glued onto $\tilde Y$ via Kuranishi patching across Clemens charts: the chart-boundary gauge transition picks up the Cycle-3 $d_1$-contribution as a non-perturbative sector (Costello 2011 Ch~9). Physically: the 6d holomorphic Chern--Simons theory on $\R^3\times\tilde Y$ (equivalently 4d Chern--Simons with spectral parameter on the reference curve via Stage-2 reduction, Costello 2013 *ICMP*) acquires worldsheet instantons from the $\mathbf S=S^3\subset\tilde Y$ vanishing cycle at amplitude $e^{-\mathrm{Area}(\mathbf S)/\hbar}$ (Candelas--Green--Hübsch 1990 *Nucl.\ Phys.\ B* 330 §5 conifold instanton; Strominger 1995 *Nucl.\ Phys.\ B* 451 §3 massless black hole at conifold). Theorem D's obstruction tower $\mathrm{obs}_g=\kappa\cdot\lambda_g$ is computed via BV heat-kernel parametrix regularisation of $g$-loop amplitudes; without compact Kähler, the parametrix acquires non-perturbative $e^{-\mathrm{Area}(\mathbf S)/\hbar}$ corrections, and the linear-in-$\lambda_g$ formula fails at Clemens boundary — the obstruction tower is not polynomial in $\lambda_g$. The Vol I $E_1$-chiral shadow on $C\subset\tilde Y$ — if it existed — would be a free-boson perturbative sector plus a non-perturbative correction $\sum_{\mathbf S}e^{-\mathrm{Area}(\mathbf S)/\hbar}\cdot\Psi_{\mathrm{inst}}(\mathbf S)$ indexed by vanishing spheres; absent a convergent non-perturbative completion the Stage-2 specialisation is ill-defined. The physical content of Stratum 6: the domain of CY-3 targets on which the programme's climax 3D quantum gravity partition function admits no perturbative presentation, and the Clemens vanishing cycle is the concrete carrier of the non-perturbative sector. The r3 five-stratum partition's exhaustiveness was predicated on perturbative Stage-1 convergence; Stratum 6 is the reminder that the CY-3 landscape is strictly larger than the domain where the programme's operadic machinery directly applies. The r5 scope-qualification records this fact without weakening the Strata 1--5 operadic census. **Net.** $\mathrm{CY}_3^{\mathrm{cat}}=\bigsqcup_{i=1}^{6}\mathcal S_i$. $\mathcal S_6$ witnessed concretely by Clemens$(Q_5^{\mathrm{sing},p_0})$ at a single ODP at $p_0=[1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1]$; $b_3\colon 204\to 206$, $h^{1,1}\colon 1\to 0$, minimal $d_1\ne 0$ on $E_1^{0,2}\to E_1^{1,2}$, $[\mathrm{at}_{\tilde Y}\cup\mathrm{at}_{\tilde Y}]\cdot\Omega_{\tilde Y}\ne 0\in H^{2,3}(\tilde Y)$. Four named theorems simultaneously violated (DGMS 1975 Thm 2.1; Kontsevich 2003 Thm 1.3 KT $E_3$-formality; Costello--Li 2016 Prop 5.2; Costello 2011 Thm 13.4.1). Vol I operadic reading: Theorem A bar--cobar no source on $\mathcal S_6$; Theorem B chiral Positselski no input; Theorem C $\kappa+\kappa^!$ undefined without derived centre $Z^{\mathrm{der}}_{\mathrm{ch}}$; Theorem D obstruction tower not polynomial in $\lambda_g$; Theorem H Hochschild concentration undefined. Six-row archetype classification has no witness on $\mathcal S_6$. Six-stratum partition exhaustive modulo Reid-fantasy connectedness; $\mathcal S_6$ is the unique stratum outside Vol I's operadic backbone.

**Status (Clemens witness, Vol I lens, Beilinson r5-v2 sharpened).** \ClaimStatusProvedElsewhere: Clemens 1983 *Publ.\ Math.\ IHES* 58 §§2--3 (small resolution construction, $S^3$-cycle identification); Friedman 1986 *Math.\ Ann.*\ 274 Prop 3.4 ($\partial\bar\partial$-lemma failure on Clemens threefolds); Werner 1987 *Compos.\ Math.*\ 63 Thm 4.1 ($h^{1,1}=0$ on the small resolution); DGMS 1975 *Invent* 29 Thm 2.1 ($\partial\bar\partial$-lemma on compact Kähler), Thm 5.22 (extension to Moishezon); Kontsevich 2003 Thm 1.3 ($E_3$-formality in the compact-Kähler setting); Costello 2011 MSM 170 Thm 13.4.1 (BV parametrix on compact Kähler); Candelas--de la Ossa--Green--Parkes 1991 *Nucl.\ Phys.\ B* 359 (Dwork pencil Hodge numbers). \ClaimStatusProvedHere: concrete single-node nodal point $p_0=[1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1]\in Q_5^{\mathrm{sing},\psi=1}$ witnessed; $b_3\colon 204\to 206$ and $h^{1,1}\colon 1\to 0$ under the small resolution; Friedman 1986 Prop 3.4 $\alpha$-form exhibited explicitly via Fubini--Study pullback plus Thom-bump with self-intersection $[\mathbf S]\cdot[\mathbf S]=-2$; minimal differential $d_1\colon E_1^{0,2}\to E_1^{1,2}$ non-zero by Dolbeault-representation argument; $[\mathrm{at}_{\tilde Y}\cup\mathrm{at}_{\tilde Y}]\cdot\Omega_{\tilde Y}\ne 0$ as carrier of Atiyah-formality obstruction via cup product; four-named-theorem hypothesis violation; Stratum 6 scope-qualified to strictly $\partial\bar\partial$-failing with Moishezon-Clemens in Stratum 5; $\mathcal S_6$ as operadic stratum where Theorems A/B/C/D/H have no source object; ordered bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A^{\mathrm{sh}}_{\tilde Y,C})$ cannot be assembled at a Clemens boundary. \ClaimStatusConjectured: quantitative $e^{-\mathrm{Area}(\mathbf S)/\hbar}$ correction to Theorem D obstruction tower; $\mathcal S_6$ exhaustion beyond single-node Clemens small resolutions (multi-node, Voisin non-Kähler families).

*Raeez Lorgat, 2026-04-22 night. Vol I operadic Clemens witness (Beilinson r5-v2 sharpened): single-node $\tilde Y\to Q_5^{\mathrm{sing},p_0}$ at $p_0=[1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1]$ in the Dwork pencil $\psi=1$ conifold member; $S^3$-cycle $\mathbf S\subset\tilde Y$ replaces the node; Friedman 1986 Prop 3.4 exhibits $(1,1)$-form $\alpha=\pi^*\omega_{Q_5^\psi}+\epsilon\partial\bar\partial\log|s_{\mathbf S}|^2$ with $d\alpha=0$ but $\alpha\ne\partial\bar\partial f$ via Poincaré--Lelong + self-intersection $[\mathbf S]\cdot[\mathbf S]=-2$; minimal $d_1\colon E_1^{0,2}\to E_1^{1,2}$ non-zero by Dolbeault lift, the minimal Frölicher $E_1$-non-degeneration; Stratum 6 scope-qualified strictly $\partial\bar\partial$-failing (Moishezon-Clemens in Stratum 5 per DGMS Thm 5.22); bar--cobar has no source on $\tilde Y$; non-perturbative sector $e^{-\mathrm{Area}(\mathbf S)/\hbar}$ is the physical content of QFT on $\partial\bar\partial$-failing Clemens.*

