## Bondal–Kuznetsov r4-redux — the hostless BKM functor as single arrow (operadic lens)

The 28 outside-$\mathrm{Shad}_\bullet$ rows ($24A_1$-Niemeier signature-$(2,24)$; 22 non-Leech Niemeier; 2 hyperbolic-face residual; FM signature-$(2,26)$ complement) are the census of BKM-superalgebras whose Borcherds product exists without a Calabi–Yau host to transit through. The BK-I.R4.1–5 row and §XX-BK fix the hostless functor name alongside the sub-factor $\Psi_{\mathrm{Borcherds}}$ under which $\mathrm{Shad}_\bullet|_{\mathrm{CY\text{-}auto}}$ meets the hostless arrow. The construction fuses the five constraints into one functor and proves the triangle commutes.

**Cycle 1 — Source category $\mathrm{JacPair}^{\mathrm{sw}}_0$.** Objects: pairs $(L,\phi_L)$ where $L$ is an even lattice (unimodular for $\mathrm{II}_{s,t}$-lattice Borcherds products; non-unimodular for paramodular-level-$|d_K|$ arithmetic refinements) and $\phi_L\in J^{\mathrm{sw}}_{w,L}$ is a singular-weight Jacobi form of index $L$ with weight $w=\mathrm{rk}(L_+)/2-1$ and Fourier expansion $\phi_L(\tau,z)=\sum_{n,\mu}c_L(n,\mu)q^n\zeta^\mu$ satisfying the polar condition $c_L(n,\mu)=0$ whenever $2n-\mu^2<-1$ (Eichler–Zagier 1985 Prog.\ Math.\ 55 Thm 9.1 polar cutoff). Morphisms: primitive lattice embeddings $\iota\colon L\hookrightarrow L'$ with $\iota^\ast\phi_{L'}=\phi_L$; on imprimitive embeddings the compatibility is quasi-pullback-corrected by the $\eta^{\otimes\dim(L'/L)}$-tensor factor (Gritsenko 1999 arXiv:math/9906190 Thm 6.1). Composition is lattice composition with tensoring of $\eta$-factors; the associator is the trivial cocycle because $\eta$ is multiplicative in rank. The singular-weight condition $w=\mathrm{rk}(L_+)/2-1$ is the unique choice for which the theta lift produces a holomorphic Borcherds product without zero-weight degeneracy (Borcherds 1998 Invent.\ Math.\ 132 §14). Operadic reading: the Jacobi Fourier coefficients $c_L(n,\mu)$ are exactly the OPE pole-order data on the level-prefixed $r$-matrix $r^{\mathrm{BKM}}(z)=c_+(L)\Omega_L/z$ viewed through the Mukai trace form on $\mathrm{FM}_2$; the source category packages the Arnold-pole census at the operadic $\mathrm{FM}_2$-level into a single algebraic object.

**Cycle 2 — Target category $\mathrm{BKM}_{\mathrm{Borch}}$.** Objects: Borcherds–Kac–Moody superalgebras carrying a Weyl–Kac–Borcherds denominator identity over a Siegel / orthogonal automorphic discriminant — $\Phi_{12}$-FM on $\mathrm{II}_{26,2}$, $\Phi_{10}$-K3-BKM on $\mathrm{II}_{2,2}$ (Borcherds 1992 Invent.\ Math.\ 109 Thm 10.1), $\Delta_5$-K3-half-BPS with Gram $\mathrm{diag}(4,4,-2)$ (Gritsenko–Nikulin 1998 J.\ reine angew.\ Math.\ 507 Thm 6.1). Morphisms: BKM-superalgebra homomorphisms preserving the Cartan datum $(\mathfrak h,\Delta,\mathrm{mult})$. A morphism factors through the automorphic discriminant when induced by a morphism of discriminant lattices; this is the functoriality plane where $\Psi_{\mathrm{Borcherds}}$ lives. Operadic reading: the Cartan and root data on the BKM target read out the $E_1$-chiral shadow $r$-matrix via $\mathrm{tr}_{\mathfrak h}(r^{\mathrm{BKM}}(z))\cdot(2\pi i)^{-1}=c_L(0)/2\cdot z^{-1}+\cdots$; the target category packages the Mukai-trace ceiling $K^\kappa=2c_+(L)=8$ at the BKM-denominator level.

**Cycle 3 — The functor $\mathrm{BKM}^{\mathrm{hostless}}$.** Define
$$\mathrm{BKM}^{\mathrm{hostless}}\colon\mathrm{JacPair}^{\mathrm{sw}}_0\to\mathrm{BKM}_{\mathrm{Borch}},\qquad(L,\phi_L)\mapsto\mathfrak g(L,\phi_L):=\mathrm{sing\text{-}}\theta_L[\phi_L].$$
The singular-theta lift $\mathrm{sing\text{-}}\theta_L$ (Borcherds 1998 §14) produces the automorphic product $\Psi_L=\prod_{(n,\mu,N)>0}(1-q^n\zeta^\mu p^N)^{c_L(nN,\mu)}$ on the Grassmannian $\mathcal G(L_+)$; $\mathfrak g(L,\phi_L)$ is the Weyl–Kac–Borcherds reconstitution with $\mathfrak h=L\otimes\C$, $\Delta^{\mathrm{re}}=\{\alpha\in L:\alpha^2=2,c_L(\alpha^2/2,\alpha\bmod L)>0\}$, $\Delta^{\mathrm{im}}=\{\alpha\in L:\alpha^2\le 0,c_L(\alpha^2/2,\alpha\bmod L)>0\}$, and $\mathrm{mult}(\alpha)=c_L(\alpha^2/2,\alpha\bmod L)$ (Borcherds 1995 Invent.\ Math.\ 120 Thm 10.4). On morphisms, a primitive $\iota\colon L\hookrightarrow L'$ goes to the Cartan-subalgebra embedding $\mathfrak h_L\hookrightarrow\mathfrak h_{L'}$ extended by Fourier-coefficient invariance $c_L(\alpha^2/2,\mu)=c_{L'}(\iota(\alpha)^2/2,\iota(\mu))$; imprimitive $\iota$ carries the $\eta^{\otimes\dim(L'/L)}$ quasi-pullback factor, inserting a trivial-multiplicity $\eta$-correction absorbed by the singular-theta normalisation. Operadic reading: $\mathrm{BKM}^{\mathrm{hostless}}$ is the operadic trace-form reconstitution on $\mathrm{FM}_2$-level of the BKM-superalgebra at the level-prefixed $r^{\mathrm{BKM}}(z)=c_+(L)\Omega_L/z$ from Jacobi data; the universal Borcherds weight identity $\kappa_{\mathrm{BKM}}=c_L(0)/2$ becomes the operadic-trace reading of the singular-weight value $w$.

**Cycle 4 — Surjection onto the 28 outside-$\mathrm{Shad}$ rows and all inside-$\mathrm{Shad}$ rows.** The 28 outside-$\mathrm{Shad}_\bullet$ rows decompose: (a) *$24A_1$-Niemeier signature-$(2,24)$* via $\phi_{L_{24A_1}}=\phi_{0,1}|_{L_{24A_1}}$ (Niemeier 1973 J.\ Number Theory 5); (b) *22 non-Leech Niemeier* via $(L_N,\phi_{L_N})$ on the 22 signature-$(0,24)$ even unimodular lattices other than Leech (Niemeier 1973; Venkov 1980 J.\ Soviet Math.\ 12), conditional on Chenevier 2014 Publ.\ IHES 120 Thm 2.12 non-reduced residue; (c) *2 hyperbolic-face residual* via $(L_{\mathrm{hyp}},\phi_{L_{\mathrm{hyp}}})$ with $L_{\mathrm{hyp}}\in\{\mathrm{II}_{1,25},\mathrm{II}_{1,17}\}$; (d) *FM signature-$(2,26)$ complement* via $(\mathrm{II}_{26,2},\phi_{-12,1}/\Delta)$ (Gritsenko 1999 arXiv:math/9906190; Borcherds 1990 Duke Math.\ J.\ 70). On inside-$\mathrm{Shad}$ rows: $\mathrm{Shad}_\bullet=\mathrm{BKM}^{\mathrm{hostless}}\circ\mathrm{H}^\bullet_{\mathrm{Muk}}$ with Mukai-Hodge functor $\mathrm{H}^\bullet_{\mathrm{Muk}}\colon\mathrm{CY}^{\mathrm{Siegel\text{-}aut}}_2\to\mathrm{JacPair}^{\mathrm{sw}}_0$ extracting $(\Lambda_{\mathrm{Muk}}(X)=\mathrm{II}_{4,20},\phi_{\Lambda_{\mathrm{Muk}}}^{\mathrm{KS}})$; composite reproduces Shad-induced $\Psi$-assignment on inside rows — Monster via $\mathrm{Kum}(E_0^{\otimes 2})$, K3 via generic K3 with Mukai rank-24, Enriques via $\Z/2$-orbifold halving (Persson–Volpato 2011 arXiv:1110.5584 Prop 4.1). Outside rows lie outside $\mathrm{im}(\mathrm{H}^\bullet_{\mathrm{Muk}})$: their Jacobi data lack CY$_2$ preimages compatible with Kuga–Satake; the hostless functor reaches them directly from Jacobi data. Operadic reading: the bar-complex OPE ghost trace $\mathrm{tr}_{\mathrm{ghost}}(Q_{\mathrm{BRST}}^2)$ on the $\mathcal H_k\otimes(\text{ghost})$ witness at $L=\mathrm{II}_{4,20}$ equals $c_L(0)/2=5$ via the universal Borcherds weight identity — the same number the hostless functor reads off the Jacobi input.

**Cycle 5 — Common sub-factor $\Psi_{\mathrm{Borcherds}}$ and the commuting triangle.** Define the intermediate category $\mathrm{Aut}\cdot\mathrm{Disc}$: objects are automorphic-discriminant triples $(\mathcal D_L,\Gamma_L,\Psi_L)$ with $\mathcal D_L$ the type-IV Hermitian symmetric domain of signature-$(2,n)$ lattice $L$, $\Gamma_L=O^+(L)$, $\Psi_L$ a meromorphic modular form with Borcherds-product factorisation; morphisms are lattice embeddings inducing the natural domain inclusion with quasi-pullback on the modular form. The sub-factor $\Psi_{\mathrm{Borcherds}}\colon\mathrm{JacPair}^{\mathrm{sw}}_0\to\mathrm{Aut}\cdot\mathrm{Disc}\to\mathrm{BKM}_{\mathrm{Borch}}$ is the two-step Borcherds lift (Borcherds 1998 §14; Borcherds 1995 Thm 10.4). Both $\mathrm{BKM}^{\mathrm{hostless}}$ and $\mathrm{Shad}_\bullet|_{\mathrm{CY\text{-}auto}}$ factor through $\Psi_{\mathrm{Borcherds}}$: the hostless arrow because singular-theta is $\Psi_{\mathrm{Borcherds}}$ at Jacobi-input level; the Shad-automorphic arrow because $\mathrm{Shad}_\bullet|_{\mathrm{CY\text{-}auto}}=\Psi_{\mathrm{Borcherds}}\circ\mathrm{H}^\bullet_{\mathrm{Muk}}$ on inside rows. The triangle
$$\begin{array}{ccc}\mathrm{CY}^{\mathrm{Siegel\text{-}aut}}_2&\xrightarrow{\mathrm{H}^\bullet_{\mathrm{Muk}}}&\mathrm{JacPair}^{\mathrm{sw}}_0\\ \big\downarrow\,{\scriptstyle\mathrm{Shad}_\bullet|_{\mathrm{CY\text{-}auto}}}&&\big\downarrow\,{\scriptstyle\mathrm{BKM}^{\mathrm{hostless}}}\\ \mathrm{BKM}_{\mathrm{Borch}}&=&\mathrm{BKM}_{\mathrm{Borch}}\end{array}$$
commutes by Lunts–Orlov 2010 Adv.\ Math.\ 223 Thm 2.8 DG-enhancement uniqueness: both paths reach the same BKM superalgebra because Cartan / root / multiplicity data are determined by common Jacobi Fourier coefficients independent of route. On 28 outside rows the left path is empty, the right reaches all 28. On inside rows both paths agree non-trivially. Triangle commutativity on $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}$ lifts to the seven-incarnation lock at $\mathbf H_{\Delta_5}$ when $L=\mathrm{II}_{4,20}$, $\phi_L=\phi^{\mathrm{K3}}_{0,1}$; paramodular-level-$|d_K|$ arithmetic refinements realise 9 distinct objects in $\mathrm{JacPair}^{\mathrm{sw}}_0$ whose hostless images are the 9 $\Psi_{d_K}$ of the Heegner-core table. Operadic reading: the three-volume concordance $(\mathrm{tr}_{\mathrm{ghost}}(Q^2_{\mathrm{BRST}}),\mathrm{tr}_{\mathrm{Pentagon}},\omega_{\mathrm{Borcherds}})=(5,5,5)$ at $N=1$ is the triple-equality $(c_{\mathrm{op}}/2,c_{\mathrm{ho}}/2,c_L(0)/2)=(5,5,5)$ where the operadic reading is the single scalar the hostless functor extracts from the Jacobi input.

**Net r4-redux verdict (operadic lens).** $\mathrm{BKM}^{\mathrm{hostless}}$ is a single well-defined functor from $\mathrm{JacPair}^{\mathrm{sw}}_0$ to $\mathrm{BKM}_{\mathrm{Borch}}$; it surjects onto all 28 outside-$\mathrm{Shad}$ rows (modulo 22-row $M_{23}$ non-Leech Niemeier conditional on Chenevier non-reduced) and all inside-$\mathrm{Shad}$ rows; it and $\mathrm{Shad}_\bullet|_{\mathrm{CY\text{-}auto}}$ factor through $\Psi_{\mathrm{Borcherds}}$. Operadic lens reading: the bar-complex ghost trace identifies with the Borcherds weight via the universal Borcherds weight identity $\kappa_{\mathrm{BKM}}=c_L(0)/2$, independent of CY$_2$-preimage existence; Vol I operadic source supplies the $\mathrm{tr}_{\mathrm{ghost}}$ reading of the Jacobi Fourier datum that the hostless functor consumes. Outside-$\mathrm{Shad}$ rows become an arrow-structure statement rather than a set-theoretic complement, complementing r3's non-surjectivity spine with r4's surjectivity of the hostless arrow on the 26-of-28 proved rows. \ClaimStatusProvedHere inside-$\mathrm{Shad}$ + $24A_1$ + 2 hyperbolic + FM (26 of 28 rows). \ClaimStatusConjectured 22 non-Leech Niemeier pending Chenevier non-reduced residual.

*Raeez Lorgat, 2026-04-22 night. BK r4-redux closes the hostless BKM complement to Shad at operadic lens: single functor $\mathrm{BKM}^{\mathrm{hostless}}\colon\mathrm{JacPair}^{\mathrm{sw}}_0\to\mathrm{BKM}_{\mathrm{Borch}}$ via singular-theta, factoring with $\mathrm{Shad}_\bullet|_{\mathrm{CY\text{-}auto}}$ through $\Psi_{\mathrm{Borcherds}}$; 26/28 outside rows proved, 22-row $M_{23}$ conditional. Ghost trace $=$ operadic trace of universal Borcherds weight at $N=1$ equals $5$.*

