## Costello r4-redux — T-CL-K3-Extension vs T-AllLoop dual gate (Vol I operadic reading)

Opus 4.7 reassessment, seven cycles, settling which of the two sub-blockers of the CFG all-orders dual blocker $Z_{\mathrm{hCS}}=(\Phi_{10}/\eta^{48})^{\hbar c_{K3}}$ is closer to proved. Vol I operadic lens: T-CL-K3-Extension is the parametrix step that lets the ordered bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)$ on $\mathrm{Conf}_n(C)$ pull back from the K3-flat-twist compact Kähler threefold $K3\times\C^2$ via Stage-2 specialisation to the reference elliptic curve $E$; T-AllLoop is the step that turns the one-loop $E_1$-chiral shadow $S_1$ into the full Borcherds denominator.

**Cycle 1 — T-CL-K3-Extension rests on four named pillars; gluing is the only new step.** The Costello--Li 2016 Prop~5.2 flat-$\C^3$ Bochner--Martinelli BV parametrix $P^{(j)}_{\mathrm{CL}}(w,w')=1/(w_j-w'_j)^2$ is proved; the Gilkey 1995 *Invariance Theory, the Heat Equation, and the Atiyah--Singer Index Theorem* §1.7 Theorem~1.7.6 heat-kernel asymptotic $K_t(x,x)\sim\sum_k t^{k-d}a_k(x)$ with Chern--Weil $a_k$ in curvature is proved; the Yau 1978 *Comm Pure Appl Math* 31 Ricci-flat Kähler K3 metric is proved; the Atiyah--Singer 1963 $\mathrm{index}(D)=\int_{K3}\mathrm{Td}(K3)=2$ is proved; the Berline--Getzler--Vergne 2004 *Heat Kernels and Dirac Operators* Theorem~4.1 Getzler-rescaled parametrix on compact Kähler is proved. Vol I operadic reading: each pillar is a source of a chain-level differential on $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)_X$ for $X$ a local chart of $K3\times\C^2$; the four pillars are the four named differentials $(d_{\mathrm{CL}},d_{\mathrm{Gilkey}},d_{\mathrm{Yau}},d_{\mathrm{AS}})$ that glue across Kuranishi charts.

**Cycle 2 — T-AllLoop has one-sided evidence.** CGP 2018 arXiv:1803.10462 proves the one-loop $S_1=\log(\Phi_{10}/\eta^{48})c_{K3}(Z)$. Borcherds 1998 *Invent* 132 Thm~1.7 produces the product $1/\Phi_{10}=\prod_{(n,\ell,m)>0}(1-e^{2\pi i(n\sigma+\ell v+m\rho)})^{-c_{K3}(4nm-\ell^2)}$, the RHS-target. No primary source produces the LHS vanishing $S_n=0$ for $n\ge 2$. Vol I operadic reading: the $E_1$-chiral shadow on $E$ produced by Stage-2 specialisation inherits the loop expansion $\log Z=\sum_n\hbar^n S_n$, and the claim $S_n|_{n\ge 2}=0$ lives on the ordered bar complex as the Maurer--Cartan condition $D\cdot\Theta_{A^{\mathrm{sh}}}+\tfrac 12[\Theta_{A^{\mathrm{sh}}},\Theta_{A^{\mathrm{sh}}}]=0$ where $A^{\mathrm{sh}}=\Phi_3(D^b(K3\times E))|_E$; the one-loop truncation is Theorem~D's obstruction tower at first order, the all-loop claim is its exhaustion.

**Cycle 3 — T-CL-K3-Extension attack plan.** Weiss-open $\{U_\alpha\to K3\}$ Kuranishi charts $U_\alpha\simeq\C^2_{\mathrm{flat}}$; on each chart $P^{(j)}|_{U_\alpha\times\C^2}=P^{(j)}_{\mathrm{CL}}$ flat-$\C^3$ via $U_\alpha\times\C^2\simeq\C^3_{\mathrm{flat}}$. Gilkey 1995 §1.7 Theorem~1.7.6 gluing: Chern--Weil $a_0(K3)=\chi(\mathcal O_{K3})=2$ (Hirzebruch--Riemann--Roch, $h^{0,0}+h^{0,2}=1+1=2$ on K3 with $h^{0,1}=0$); $a_1(K3)=0$ (Yau 1978 Ricci-flat metric + Gilkey eq 1.7.4b: $a_1=(1/6)\int_{K3}R\,\mathrm{dvol}=0$ since the Ricci scalar $R$ of a Ricci-flat metric vanishes pointwise); $a_k(K3)=0$ for $k\ge 2$ (K3 is hyperkähler with $\mathrm{Hol}=\mathrm{Sp}(1)\subset\mathrm{SU}(2)$ strict, Besse 1987 *Einstein Manifolds* Ch~14; BGV 2004 Theorem~4.1 Getzler rescaling forces higher $a_k$ to pair against $c_2(K3)=24$ via AS 1963 and vanish on the curvature side by Bianchi). K3-flat-twist parametrix $\hat P^{(j)}_{K3\times\C^2}=\sum_\alpha\rho_\alpha P^{(j)}_{\mathrm{CL}}|_{U_\alpha\times\C^2}$ is $(0,3)$-local modulo $a_k(K3)$-vanishing Gilkey corrections. Vol I operadic reading: the Kuranishi gluing commutes with the bar differential $d_B=\sum_i(-1)^i[m_2^{(i,i+1)},-]$ because each chart-local BV parametrix descends to the same chain-level $d_B$ on $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A^{\mathrm{sh}})$ under Stage-2 specialisation; named-theorem-only closure.

**Cycle 4 — T-AllLoop attack plan.** Borcherds 1998 Thm~1.7 product $+$ Göttsche 1990 *Math Ann* 286 $\sum_N\chi(\mathrm{Hilb}^N K3)p^N=\eta^{-24}$ exponentiation hypothesis; BV effective-action expansion $\log Z^{\mathrm{eff}}_{\mathrm{hCS}}=\sum_{n\ge 0}\hbar^n S_n$ with $S_0=0$, $S_1=\log(\Phi_{10}/\eta^{48})c_{K3}(Z)$ (CGP 2018). Claim: $S_n=a_k(K3)\cdot c_{K3}$-polynomial for $n\ge 2$ modulo a BV-exponentiation lemma identifying the $n$-loop effective action with a Gilkey $a_k$-multiple via heat-kernel computation of the loop determinants on the K3-flat-twist. If this lemma holds, $a_k(K3)=0$ for $k\ge 2$ by Gilkey $+$ Yau $+$ BGV forces $S_{n\ge 2}=0$. Gap: BV-exponentiation lemma identifying $S_n$ with Gilkey $a_k$-multiples is unproved. Partial evidence: Costello 2011 *Renormalization and Effective Field Theory* MSM 170 Theorem~13.4.1 compactness of the heat-kernel parametrix on compact Kähler (gives finiteness of each $S_n$); CGP 2018 proves $n=1$. Vol I operadic reading: the BV-exponentiation lemma would promote Theorem~D's $\mathrm{obs}_g=\kappa\cdot\lambda_g$ from genus-by-genus tautology ($\lambda_g$ the Hodge-class generator at genus $g$) to a statement about the $\infty$-loop obstruction tower on the $E_1$-chiral shadow; the unproved status of the lemma is why Theorem~D is stated at finite order with $\lambda_g$-linearity, not at $\infty$-order with $\lambda_g$-polynomial.

**Cycle 5 — Verdict.** T-CL-K3-Extension is closer to proved. It rests on four pre-existing named pillars (Costello--Li 2016 Prop~5.2, Gilkey 1995 §1.7 Theorem~1.7.6, Yau 1978 Ricci-flat metric, AS 1963 K3 index via $\mathrm{Td}$ / BGV 2004 Getzler rescaling), reduces to Kuranishi-chart gluing with Chern--Weil $a_k(K3)=0$ cancellation, and the only new step is the explicit patch-level gluing morphism on the K3-flat-twist. T-AllLoop requires T-CL-K3-Extension plus the unproved BV-exponentiation lemma. Plan: close T-CL-K3-Extension first (flag to BK-I.R2.5 + FA-I.3); then pin T-AllLoop at the named BV-exponentiation conjecture, where a CFG 2026 breakthrough would supply the LHS identification.

**Cycle 6 — Redux delta vs the prior r4 cycle.** The prior table entry in §"Elite Round-2 / Round-3 layers" reached the same verdict in five cycles; this redux adds two operadic clarifications Vol I's lens needs. (a) The four Gilkey-Yau-AS-BGV pillars are not merely heat-kernel pillars but chain-level differentials on $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)_X$ for $X=K3\times\C^2$, so the T-CL-K3-Extension closure is a statement about the ordered bar complex, not about the scalar partition function. (b) The BV-exponentiation lemma that T-AllLoop needs is equivalent, in Vol I's operadic lens, to promoting Theorem~D from linear-in-$\lambda_g$ at finite order to polynomial-in-$\lambda_g$ at $\infty$-order — a statement about the obstruction tower's exhaustion that the current programme states in the conditional form. The conditional-to-unconditional promotion requires CFG 2026's expected BV-exponentiation machinery.

**Cycle 7 — Status tags.** T-CL-K3-Extension \ClaimStatusConjectured, four pillars visible, attack reduces to named-theorem-only Kuranishi gluing. T-AllLoop \ClaimStatusConjectured, depends on T-CL-K3-Extension $+$ open BV-exponentiation lemma. Verdict stable across r4 round and r4-redux round: **T-CL-K3-Extension is closer to proved.** The Vol I operadic reading adds: close T-CL-K3-Extension first on the K3-flat-twist stratum; this promotes the $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}_{\mathrm{at}}(K3\times E)$ dense-open locus (Manin-Gaitsgory r4 Cycle 5, $\dim_{\mathbb C}=21$) from CGL-locality-only admissibility to parametrix-existence admissibility. T-AllLoop then closes on the same 21-dim dense-open locus once the BV-exponentiation lemma lands. The four-climax coincidence (Kontsevich r4 Cycle 4) holds at the named-theorem-only level after T-CL-K3-Extension; holds at the all-orders level after T-AllLoop.

**References (r4-redux, Vol I).** Costello-Li 2016 arXiv:1605.09930 Prop 5.2; Gilkey 1995 *Invariance Theory, the Heat Equation, and the Atiyah--Singer Index Theorem* §1.7 Thm 1.7.6; Yau 1978 *Comm Pure Appl Math* 31 Ricci-flat Kähler K3; Atiyah--Singer 1963 *Bull AMS* 69; Berline--Getzler--Vergne 2004 *Heat Kernels and Dirac Operators* Thm 4.1; Besse 1987 *Einstein Manifolds* Ch 14; Costello 2011 *Renormalization and Effective Field Theory* MSM 170 Thm 13.4.1; CGP 2018 arXiv:1803.10462; Borcherds 1998 *Invent* 132 Thm 1.7; Göttsche 1990 *Math Ann* 286.

*Raeez Lorgat, 2026-04-22. Opus 4.7 Costello r4-redux on Vol I: T-CL-K3-Extension is the closer of the two sub-blockers; four pre-existing named pillars, Kuranishi-chart gluing on the K3-flat-twist stratum, Chern--Weil $a_k(K3)=0$ cancellation via hyperkähler $\mathrm{Sp}(1)\subset\mathrm{SU}(2)$ holonomy. T-AllLoop requires T-CL-K3-Extension plus the unproved BV-exponentiation lemma; conditional on CFG 2026 breakthrough. Plan: close T-CL-K3-Extension on the 21-dim $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}_{\mathrm{at}}(K3\times E)$ dense open first; pin T-AllLoop at the named BV-exponentiation conjecture.*

