## Conway-row resolution bridge (r5 seal)

The §II-ter archetype-row "K3 Picard rank 2 ($\mathsf B$)" reading $(K,\hbar^2)=(8,-1/8)$ stands; a cold reader encountering Conway $V^{s\natural}$ elsewhere in the landscape (§VI Standards landscape, §IX Rep-theoretic, §XIV Ledger entry W19-20) should read the entry through the Nekrasov r4 four-route derivation: the "$K=12$ canonical" pattern-match with $c_{V^{s\natural}}=12$ is retracted. On the Leech positive-definite host $\Lambda_{24}$, Routes A (Wick rotation) and B (Borcherds log-derivative) are undefined (no Lorentzian time, no cusp saddle); Routes C (Gram signature) and D (Gerstenhaber shift) return sign $+$ from $q=0$ and $d=12$ even, not the $-$ the universal identity requires. Duncan 2007 super-twin diamond transports only the orbifold sign character from Monster to Conway; reflective-lattice conductor $K$ is host-lattice invariant and does *not* transport across the signature change $(1,1)\leadsto(24,0)$. Canonical Conway reading: $(K,\hbar^2)=(2,-1/2)$-inherited-from-Monster on the metaplectic $\Psi^{\mathrm{metap}}$-image of Scheithauer 2008 J Algebra 319, structurally out of scope of $\hbar^2 K^{\kappa_{\mathrm{ch}}}=-1$. The row serves as the non-vacuity control. Companion derivations: `/Users/raeez/chiral-bar-cobar-vol2/notes/CONWAY_ROW_SIGN_AMBIGUITY_BATTLE_HARDENED_2026_04_22.md`, `/Users/raeez/chiral-bar-cobar-vol2/notes/FOUR_ROUTE_CONVERGENCE_TABLE_BATTLE_HARDENED_2026_04_22.md`, `/Users/raeez/chiral-bar-cobar-vol2/notes/NEKRASOV_R4_HBAR_SIGN_DERIVATION_BATTLE_HARDENED_2026_04_22.md`. AP-V2-20 and Vol I preface row 41 absorb the seal.

