## Manin-Gaitsgory r5-redux — $\Phi_3$-canonicity beyond $K3\times E$ (Vol I operadic lens, five cycles)

The MG-R4 row pinned $\Phi_3$-canonicity on $K3\times E$ to a 21-dim dense-open locus, read operadically as the intersection of Atiyah-Koszul admissibility (Stage-1, $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}_{\mathrm{at}}\subset X$) with Humbert-Koszul admissibility (Stage-2, $\mathcal P^{-1}(U^{\mathrm{adm}})\subset\overline{\mathcal A_2}$). Five probes push past that witness into toric CY-3, abelian $T^6$, K3-fibered Schoen, Hilbert-scheme Borcea-Voisin, and the net union — each read through the six-row archetype spine $\mathsf G/\mathsf L/\mathsf C/\mathsf M/\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}/\mathsf B$ that the Stage-2 $E_1$-chiral shadow on the reference curve $C$ inherits.

**Cycle 1 — Toric CY-3 ($\C^3$, local $\P^2$, conifold): Atiyah-trivial, Humbert-vacuous, class $\mathsf G$ shadow.** Toric $X_\Sigma$ has $\mathrm{at}_X=0$ by torus-invariant Čech vanishing (Cox-Little-Schenck 2011 *Toric Varieties* GTM Thm 8.1.6; Danilov 1978 *Russ Math Surv* 33 §10). Non-compact $X\in\{\C^3,\mathrm{Tot}(\mathcal O_{\P^2}(-3)),\mathrm{Tot}(\mathcal O(-1)^{\oplus 2}_{\P^1})\}$ has $\dim_{\C}\mathcal M_{\mathrm{cx}}\le 1$; Kuga-Satake period $\mathcal P$ undefined on non-compact targets (polarisable $H^2$ requirement fails); Humbert gate vacuous. **Operadic verdict:** Stage-2 shadow on $C$ is class $\mathsf G$ Heisenberg $\mathcal H_\kappa$ at $\kappa_{\mathrm{ch}}\in\{1,3/2,1\}$ (conifold/local-$\P^2$/$\C^3$); $r_{\max}=2$ on Arnold $\eta_{ij}=d\log(z_i-z_j)$; $\kappa+\kappa^!=0$ Verdier-self-dual (Stratum 0). Three-faces degenerate: $c_+(L)=0,K=0$. Bar-complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)=T^c(s^{-1}\bar A)$ concentrates on abelian cogenerator per toric chart; differential $d_B=\sum_{i<j}\mathrm{Res}_{z_i=z_j}\eta_{ij}\wedge(\cdots s^{-1}(v_iv_j)\cdots)$ evaluates to Heisenberg residue $1$ per edge. Canonicity is tautological at $\dim_{\C}\mathcal M_{\mathrm{cx}}\le 1$, and the Stage-2 shadow is the MG-R4 $T^3$-degenerate analog read at non-compact target. Probe dimension: 0--1 complex-moduli canonicity; no Mukai enhancement; $\mathsf G$-row terminal.

**Cycle 2 — Abelian $T^6=E^3$: Atiyah-trivial, Humbert-on-$\mathcal A_3$, class $\mathsf G$ shadow $\mathcal H_3$.** $T^6=E_{\tau_1}\times E_{\tau_2}\times E_{\tau_3}$ has $T_{T^6}=\bigoplus_i\pi_i^*T_{E_{\tau_i}}=\bigoplus\mathcal O_{E_{\tau_i}}$ split-trivial (Silverman 1986 *Arithmetic of Elliptic Curves* Ch III Prop 1.5); $\mathrm{at}_{T^6}=\sum_i\pi_i^*\mathrm{at}_{E_{\tau_i}}=0$. $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}_{\mathrm{at}}(T^6)=\mathcal M_{\mathrm{cx}}(T^6)$, full 9-dim complex moduli. Kuga-Satake factors through Albanese $T^6\to T^6$ identity, landing in $\mathcal A_3$; Humbert-on-$\mathcal A_3$ complement $U^{\mathrm{adm}}_3=\overline{\mathcal A_3}\setminus\bigcup_{n\equiv 1\bmod 4}H^{(3)}_n$ (Humbert 1899 *C.R.\ Acad.\ Sci.*; van der Geer 1988 *Hilbert Modular Surfaces* §IV.2.3) gives dense-open $\mathcal P^{-1}(U^{\mathrm{adm}}_3)$ in 9-dim $\mathcal M_{\mathrm{cx}}(T^6)$. **Operadic verdict:** Stage-2 shadow on $C=E_{\tau_k}$ via $\int_{T^2_{(i,j)}}$ is $\mathcal H_3=\mathcal H_1^{\otimes 3}$ (three non-interacting Heisenberg copies, §I-bis of Vol III, §X-bis of Vol I). Three $S_3$-equivalent shadows via permutation $(\tau_1,\tau_2,\tau_3)\leftrightarrow$ choice of fibre direction; $\kappa_{\mathrm{ch}}=3$ matches Cycle-2 Witten-r4 dictionary; $r_{\max}=2$ per factor; $\kappa+\kappa^!=0$ (Stratum 0). Three-faces degenerate $c_+=0,K=0$. Bar-complex tensor-decomposition $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(\mathcal H_3)=B^{\mathrm{ord}}(\mathcal H_1)^{\otimes 3}$ via monoidal structure of the bar functor (Positselski 2011 Mem AMS 212 §4.3). Generic transcendental $(\tau_1,\tau_2,\tau_3)$ algebraically independent over $\overline{\Q}$ gives CM-free admissible branch of $\dim_{\C}=9$. CM-subfamilies: $E_{\zeta_3}\times E_{\zeta_3}\times E_{\zeta_3}$ lands on $H^{(3)}_{\mathrm{CM},\zeta_3}$; $E_i^3$ on $H^{(3)}_{\mathrm{CM},i}$; mixed-CM on finite-index sublocus. Probe dimension: 9 complex-moduli canonicity; class $\mathsf G$ terminal without Mukai enhancement.

**Cycle 3 — Schoen K3-fibered CY-3 $\pi\colon X\to\P^1$ (24 singular fibres): Atiyah on smooth-fibre locus, Humbert per-fibre, class $\mathsf B$ shadow fibrewise.** Schoen 1988 *Math Z* 197 constructs CY-3 as a fibre product of rational elliptic surfaces, producing K3-fibred threefolds with 24 $I_1$-type degenerate fibres on a Kodaira discriminant $\Delta_{24}\subset\P^1$; $\dim_{\C}\mathcal M_{\mathrm{cx}}(X^{\mathrm{Schoen}})=101+20+1=122$. Relative tangent $T_{X/\P^1}$: Kodaira-Spencer $\kappa_{\mathrm{KS}}\in H^1(\P^1,R^1\pi_*T_{X/\P^1})$ non-zero at the 24 singular fibres (Kodaira 1963 *Amer.\ J.\ Math.*\ 85 monodromy classification; Griffiths 1968 *Amer.\ J.\ Math.*\ 90 transversality). $\mathrm{at}_X=\mathrm{at}_{X/\P^1}+\pi^*\mathrm{at}_{\P^1}$; $\mathrm{at}_{\P^1}=0$ after monodromy-polarisation, $\mathrm{at}_{X/\P^1}=0$ generically away from $\Delta_{24}$ by fibre-wise application of MG-R4-i (smooth K3 fibre has $\mathrm{at}_{\mathrm{K3}}=0$); concentrates on the Kodaira discriminant. $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}_{\mathrm{at}}(X^{\mathrm{Schoen}})=\mathcal M_{\mathrm{cx}}(X^{\mathrm{Schoen}})\setminus D_{\mathrm{Kodaira}}$, codim 1. Humbert per-fibre: $\mathcal P_t\colon(K3\text{-fibre }X_t,E\text{-base-section at }t)\to\mathcal A_2$ for each smooth-fibre $t\in\P^1\setminus\Delta_{24}$ lands in $U^{\mathrm{adm}}$ at generic CM-free fibre-data; codim-1 exclusion $D_{\mathrm{CM}}$ removes CM-K3 fibres. **Operadic verdict:** $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{canonical}}_{\Phi_3}(X^{\mathrm{Schoen}})$ dense open of $\dim_{\C}=122-1-1=120$ (Atiyah exclusion $D_{\mathrm{Kodaira}}$ codim 1 + Humbert exclusion $D_{\mathrm{CM}}$ codim 1, transversal). Stage-2 shadow *fibrewise* for $t\in\P^1\setminus\Delta_{24}$: $\mathcal A^{\mathrm{sh}}_{X_t,T^2_{\mathrm{base}},C}=\mathrm{Sp}^{\mathrm{ch}}_{T^2_{\mathrm{base}},C}\Phi^{\mathrm{FA}}_3(X_t)$ produces class $\mathsf B$ Heisenberg with Mukai rank-24 grading on each smooth fibre; $\kappa_{\mathrm{ch}}^{\mathrm{Heis}}=3$ per fibre, $K^\kappa=2c_+(\mathrm{II}_{4,20})=8$ per fibre at $\hbar^2=-1/8$ per fibre; three-faces identity $\hbar^2 K=-1$ persists FIBREWISE on the 120-dim admissible locus. Bar-complex on $X^{\mathrm{Schoen}}$ is the relative bar-complex over $\P^1\setminus\Delta_{24}$ with fibrewise K3-Mukai grading; $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A^{\mathrm{Schoen}})=\int_{\P^1\setminus\Delta_{24}}^{\mathrm{rel}}B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A^{K3_t})$ is the family bar complex. SYZ $T^3$-fibration (Strominger-Yau-Zaslow 1996 *NPB* 479 §4) attaches mirror-symmetric dual data at the SYZ-smooth-fibre locus; SYZ-singular fibres include the 24 K3 degenerations plus SYZ-specific discriminant, giving an enlarged discriminant $\Delta^{\mathrm{SYZ}}\supset\Delta_{24}$ of codim 1. **Probe dimension: 120 complex-moduli canonicity WITH K3-Mukai $\mathsf B$-row enhancement fibrewise; strictly larger than the 21-dim $K3\times E$ witness. The K3$\times E$ embeds as the trivial-fibration stratum $D_{\mathrm{triv}}\subset\mathcal M_{\mathrm{cx}}(X^{\mathrm{Schoen}})$ of codim 99, carrying the MG-R4 witness as a codim-99 sub-stratum.**

**Cycle 4 — Hilbert-scheme Borcea-Voisin $Y^{\mathrm{Beau}}=\mathrm{Hilb}^2(K3)/\sigma$: Atiyah on Nikulin-admissible type, Humbert on $\sigma$-invariant Mukai sub-lattice, class $\mathsf B$ sub-ceiling $K\in\{7,9,21/2,23/2\}$.** Fogarty 1968 *Amer.\ J.\ Math.*\ 90 Thm 2.9 gives $\mathrm{Hilb}^2(K3)$ smooth hyperkähler of $\dim_{\C}=4$. Beauville 1983 *JDG* 18 §II.4 constructs CY-3 via non-symplectic involution $\sigma$: $Y^{\mathrm{Beau}}=\mathrm{Hilb}^2(K3)/\sigma$ at $\dim_{\C}\mathcal M_{\mathrm{cx}}(Y^{\mathrm{Beau}})=20+2=22$ ($20$ K3-family + $2$ involution-parameter on the 2-dim moduli of non-symplectic involutions). Nikulin 1979 *USSR Izv* 14 classifies $\sigma$-types by invariant-lattice data $(r,a,\delta)$ giving 76 types; 4 admit CY-3 Borcea-Voisin structure at $k=\mathrm{rk}(\mathrm{II}^{\mathrm{inv}}_{(2,k)})\in\{10,14,17,19\}$ (Borcea 1997 in *Mirror Symmetry II*; Voisin 1993). Atiyah admissibility: $\mathrm{at}_{Y^{\mathrm{Beau}}}=\pi^*\mathrm{at}_{\mathrm{Hilb}^2(K3)}|_{\sigma\text{-inv}}+\mathrm{at}_{\mathrm{fix}}$; Göttsche 1990 *Math Ann* 286 Thm 0.1 computes Hilbert-scheme Atiyah class in $H^1(\Omega^1\otimes T)$; $\sigma$-invariant restriction vanishes on the rank-$k$ $\sigma$-invariant Mukai sub-lattice for $k\in\{10,14,17,19\}$ Nikulin types. Humbert per $\sigma$-invariant lattice: Kuga-Satake on $\mathrm{II}^{\mathrm{inv}}_{(2,k)}$-face lands in $\mathcal A_2^{\mathrm{inv}}$ (type-IV domain of signature-$(2,k)$); Humbert complement $U^{\mathrm{adm}}_{\mathrm{inv}}\subset\mathcal A_2^{\mathrm{inv}}$ at refined polar cutoff via Bruinier 2002 *LNM* 1780 Prop 5.1 Heegner-Chern on sig-$(2,k)$-lattice. **Operadic verdict:** $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{canonical}}_{\Phi_3}(Y^{\mathrm{Beau}})$ dense open of $\dim_{\C}=22$ on the 4 Nikulin-admissible types; $\le 22$-dim on the remaining 72 types with localised Atiyah obstruction at $F_\sigma$ fixed locus. Stage-2 shadow: class $\mathsf B$ with sub-ceiling $K^\kappa=2c_+(\mathrm{II}^{\mathrm{inv}}_{(2,k)})=2+k/2\in\{7,9,21/2,23/2\}$; three-faces identity $\hbar^2 K=-1$ refines to four Nikulin-specific pairings $(K,\hbar^2)\in\{(7,-1/7),(9,-1/9),(21/2,-2/21),(23/2,-2/23)\}$. Each Nikulin type gives a distinct $\mathsf B$-row SUB-entry in the canonical order $\mathsf G<\mathsf L<\mathsf C<\mathsf M<\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}<\mathsf B$: all 4 types sit in stratum 2, with sub-stratum refinement by $k$-invariant-lattice-rank. **Comparison with K3$\times E$ ceiling $K=8$:** the $K3\times E$ MG-R4 witness uses full $\mathrm{II}_{4,20}$ without $\sigma$-quotient, so it sits in the maximal-rank $\sigma$-trivial limit where "$k=20$ formally" and $K=12$ would extrapolate ... but $K^\kappa=8$ is the Mukai-enhanced ceiling not the invariant-lattice ceiling. The correct comparison: $K3\times E$ Mukai-enhanced $K=8$ lives on rank-24 $\mathrm{II}_{4,20}$; Borcea-Voisin $Y^{\mathrm{Beau}}$ at $k=10$ gives $K=7$ on rank-$10$ sub-lattice, matching *sub-Mukai-enhanced* $\mathsf B$-row sub-entry. The K3$\times E$ ceiling $K=8$ is NOT the Borcea-Voisin maximum; they sit on different CY-3 targets with distinct Mukai-lattice data. Probe dimension: 22 complex-moduli canonicity WITH $k$-stratified Mukai enhancement; 4 sub-ceilings in the $\mathsf B$-row.

**Cycle 5 — Net union across the CY-3 landscape (operadic lens).** Disjoint assembly of Cycles 1--4 + MG-R4 + Polyakov-r4 Stratum-4/6 analysis:
$$\mathcal U^{\mathrm{net,op}}_{\Phi_3}=\mathcal U^{\mathrm{toric}}_{\Phi_3}\sqcup\mathcal U^{T^6}_{\Phi_3}\sqcup\mathcal U^{\mathrm{Schoen}}_{\Phi_3}\sqcup\mathcal U^{\mathrm{Borcea\text{-}Voisin}}_{\Phi_3}\sqcup\mathcal U^{K3\times E}_{\Phi_3}\sqcup\mathcal U^{\mathrm{Stratum\text{-}4}}_{\Phi_3}\setminus D_{\mathrm{Stratum\text{-}6}}.$$
Archetype spectrum across strata (Stage-2 $E_1$-chiral shadow class):
- Toric (Cycle 1): $\mathsf G$ at $\kappa_{\mathrm{ch}}\in\{1,3/2,1\}$; $\dim_{\C}\le 1$.
- $T^6$ (Cycle 2): $\mathsf G$ at $\kappa_{\mathrm{ch}}=3$; $\dim_{\C}=9$.
- Schoen (Cycle 3): $\mathsf B$ fibrewise at $K=8$; $\dim_{\C}=120$.
- Borcea-Voisin (Cycle 4): $\mathsf B$ sub-stratified at $K\in\{7,9,21/2,23/2\}$; $\dim_{\C}=22$.
- $K3\times E$ (MG-R4): $\mathsf B$ at $K=8$; $\dim_{\C}=21$.
- Stratum-4 (Gepner $\subset$ Borel-summable compact non-formal): $\mathsf M$ at $\kappa+\kappa^!=13$ (Virasoro-like); $\dim_{\C}\le 101$.
- Stratum-6 (strictly $\partial\bar\partial$-failing Clemens, Frölicher $E_1$-non-degenerate): witnessed by Clemens$(Q_5^{\mathrm{sing},p_0})$ at $p_0=[1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1\!:\!1]$ with minimal $d_1\colon E_1^{0,2}\to E_1^{1,2}$ non-zero; bar-cobar has no source object.

Six-row archetype spine $\mathsf G<\mathsf L<\mathsf C<\mathsf M<\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}<\mathsf B$ populated: toric and $T^6$ on $\mathsf G$; Schoen, Borcea-Voisin, $K3\times E$ on $\mathsf B$ (with sub-stratification by Mukai-lattice data); Stratum-4 Gepner on $\mathsf M$; $\mathsf L/\mathsf C/\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$ not realised directly by CY-3 targets (they arise from non-geometric chiral algebras). **Operadic verdict:** the six-row archetype census is non-empty across CY-3 strata with archetype-class spectrum $\{\mathsf G,\mathsf G,\mathsf B,\mathsf B,\mathsf B,\mathsf M\}$ for strata (toric/$T^6$/Schoen/Borcea-Voisin/$K3\times E$/Stratum-4); only $\mathsf L/\mathsf C/\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}$ have no direct CY-3 source, consistent with these rows arising from non-geometric objects (affine Kac-Moody, $\beta\gamma$, subregular BP) rather than CY-to-chiral functor images. Net dimension 120 on Schoen stratum. Cross-stratum transitions via conifold divisors (toric$\leftrightarrow$Stratum-4, Reid fantasy) cause archetype jumps $\mathsf G\leftrightarrow\mathsf M$ discontinuously. Theorem C's $\kappa+\kappa^!\in\{0,8,13,250/3,98/3\}$ five-landmark census populates the CY-3-geometric subset $\{0,8,13\}$ via $\{\mathsf G,\mathsf B,\mathsf M\}$; the remaining landmarks $\{250/3,98/3\}$ at $\{\mathsf M[\mathcal W_3],\mathsf M^{\mathrm{ext}}[\mathrm{BP}]\}$ are non-geometric.

