## Kapranov r5 — Hopf reduction at all arities by induction (Vol I operadic reading)

Round-3 Kapranov established the arity-2 Hopf fibration $\mathrm{FM}_4(2)\simeq S^3\twoheadrightarrow\mathrm{FM}_2(2)\simeq S^1$ with $S^2$ fibre. Round-4 extended explicitly to arity 4 via a stratified $T^3$-phase bundle with fibre $(S^2)^{\times 3}$, plus arity-3 warm-up with fibre $S^2\times S^2$. Round-5 closes the ladder: induction on $n$ from arity 2 to arity $\infty$, with Stasheff associahedron $K_{n+1}$ ($C_n$ vertices) governing the compatibility between arity-$n$ and arity-$(n+1)$ reductions, and Lurie HA.5.5 lifting the chain-level pentagon coherence to an $(\infty,1)$-operad morphism at all arities. Vol I's operadic lens reads this as the assertion that the Dolbeault reduction of Stage-1 $E_{2d}$-holomorphic factorisation algebras to Stage-2 $E_d$-real factorisation algebras is canonical at every configuration-space arity controlling the ordered bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)$ on $\mathrm{Conf}_n(C)$.

**Theorem (Kapranov-I.R5, Hopf reduction at all arities, $d=2$).** For each $n\ge 2$ the Dolbeault-Hopf reduction
$$\mathrm{Hopf}_n\colon\mathrm{FM}_4(n)\twoheadrightarrow\mathrm{FM}_2(n)$$
is a stratified $T^{n-1}$-phase bundle with total real dimension $4n-5$, base real dimension $2n-3$, and fibre $(S^2)^{\times(n-1)}$ of real dimension $2n-2$. The collection $\{\mathrm{Hopf}_n\}_{n\ge 2}$ assembles into a morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads $\mathrm{Hopf}_\bullet\colon\mathrm{FM}_4\to\mathrm{FM}_2$, coherent with the operadic composition structures on both sides; the Stasheff associahedron $K_{n+1}$ with $C_n$ vertices (Catalan number) indexes the compatibility axioms. Vol I operadic reading: on each $\mathrm{Conf}_n(C)$-arity piece of the ordered bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)=T^c(s^{-1}\bar A)$ on $\overline{\cM}_{g,n}$, the Dolbeault reduction from the complexified Stage-1 factorisation algebra on the holomorphic-topological thickening $C\times\R^2$ to the Stage-2 $E_1$-chiral shadow on $C$ is canonical at every $n$; the arity-by-arity assembly is the operadic coherence witness for Theorem A's bar-cobar adjunction on the full ordered bar complex.

**Cycle 1 — Inductive step setup.** Assume by induction that $\mathrm{Hopf}_n\colon\mathrm{FM}_4(n)\to\mathrm{FM}_2(n)$ is a proved stratified $T^{n-1}$-phase bundle morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads at arities $2,\ldots,n$. Attack arity $n+1$. Inherit the arity $n$ structure on $\partial\mathrm{FM}_2(n+1)$ codim-1 strata; lift to codim-1 strata of $\partial\mathrm{FM}_4(n+1)$ via Künneth factorisation. Adding the $(n+1)$-th leg contributes $C_n$ (Catalan) new codim-1 strata indexed by binary trees $T$ on $n+2$ leaves — each stratum takes the form $\partial_T\mathrm{FM}_d(n+1)\cong\mathrm{FM}_d(k)\times\mathrm{FM}_d(n+2-k)$ for some $k\in\{2,\ldots,n\}$ (Getzler--Jones 1994 §3; Markl--Shnider--Stasheff 2002 *Operads in Algebra, Topology and Physics* §II.1.6). The new Hopf phase collapse $S^1\to\mathrm{pt}$ on the $(n+1)$-th leg lifts to $S^3\to S^1$ via the Hopf fibration on the new directional factor; the composed fibre gains one $S^2$ factor, bringing the total fibre from $(S^2)^{\times(n-1)}$ to $(S^2)^{\times n}$. Vol I operadic reading: the added configuration leg enlarges the ordered bar complex from arity $n$ to arity $n+1$; the Koszul sign $(-1)^{|v_1|+\cdots+|v_i|}$ at position $i$ in $s^{-1}v_1\otimes\cdots\otimes s^{-1}v_{n+1}$ commutes with the added Hopf phase collapse by the Koszul-sign decoupling lemma (Loday--Vallette 2012 *Algebraic Operads* Prop 4.1.1).

**Cycle 2 — Base case arity 2 (Kapranov r3 restated).** $\mathrm{FM}_4(2)\simeq S^3$ (two ordered points in $\C^2$ modulo global translation and rescaling reduce to a unit vector in $\C^2\setminus 0$, i.e.\ $S^3$); $\mathrm{FM}_2(2)\simeq S^1$ (two ordered points in $\R^2$ modulo translation and rescaling reduce to a unit vector in $\R^2\setminus 0$, i.e.\ $S^1$); the Hopf fibration $S^3\twoheadrightarrow S^2$ (Hopf 1931 *Math Ann* 104 §4) composed with the diameter projection $S^2\twoheadrightarrow S^1$ realises $\mathrm{Hopf}_2$ with fibre $S^2$. Real dimensions: $4\cdot 2-5=3$ (total), $2\cdot 2-3=1$ (base), $2\cdot 2-2=2$ (fibre). Koszul-sign: at arity 2, $b_2(s^{-1}v_1\otimes s^{-1}v_2)=(-1)^{|v_1|}m_2(v_1,v_2)$; the Hopf phase $\zeta=e^{i\theta}\in\mathrm U(1)$ acts on $s^{-1}v_j$ by $\zeta\cdot s^{-1}v_j=e^{i\theta|v_j|}s^{-1}v_j$; Koszul sign invariant under $\zeta$-action since $b_2$ bi-linear in the shifted generators. Vol I operadic reading: on $\mathcal H_k$ at arity 2 the Arnold generator $\eta_{12}=d\log(z_1-z_2)$ descends under the Hopf phase collapse to the $\R$-direction differential $d\log|z_1-z_2|$, carrying the ordered bar differential $b_2$ to the symmetric bar differential on $\mathrm{Conf}_2(\R)$ after averaging.

**Cycle 3 — Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-coherence.** The Stasheff associahedron $K_{n+1}$ is the polytope parametrising $A_\infty$-coherent reassociations of a non-commutative word in $n+2$ letters; $K_{n+1}$ has $C_n$ vertices (Catalan number $C_n=\frac{1}{n+1}\binom{2n}{n}$), one for each binary tree on $n+2$ leaves (Stasheff 1963 *Trans AMS* 108 §2; Loday 2004 *Archiv Math* 83 §1). Pentagon $K_4$ has $C_3=5$ vertices; $K_5$ has $C_4=14$ vertices; $K_6$ has $C_5=42$; in general $K_{n+1}$ controls the arity-$(n+1)$-level pentagon-coherence axioms of an $A_\infty$-operad. At arity $n+1$, each vertex of $K_{n+1}$ labels a codim-1 stratum $\partial_T\mathrm{FM}_d(n+1)\cong\mathrm{FM}_d(k)\times\mathrm{FM}_d(n+2-k)$ for binary tree $T$ that splits $n+2$ leaves into two subtrees of $k+1$ and $n+3-k$ leaves with $2\le k\le n$. The induction hypothesis closes each such stratum: the Hopf reduction on $\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(k)\times\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n+2-k)$ factors Künneth-independently as $\mathrm{Hopf}_k\times\mathrm{Hopf}_{n+2-k}$ — the phase collapse on the $k$-factor and the $(n+2-k)$-factor are independent because the configuration-space boundary is a Cartesian product. Edges of $K_{n+1}$ connect adjacent strata via Whitehead-equivalence of binary tree reassociations; pentagon-coherence demands the Hopf reduction commute with the edge-flip composition. At arity 4, $K_4$ has 5 pentagon vertices with three of them indexed by binary trees $T_{12|34},T_{13|24},T_{14|23}$ and two reassociation-only vertices; the r4 verification covered all 5. At arity 5, $K_5$ has 14 vertices indexed by 14 binary trees on 5 leaves; pentagon edge-flips on each face commute with $T^4$ fibre collapse by Künneth + Dunn-Kontsevich $E_{2d}\to E_d$ Dolbeault rigidity (Kontsevich 1999 *Lett Math Phys* 48 Thm 1). Vol I operadic reading: the ordered bar complex's $A_\infty$-structure is controlled by $K_{n+1}$ at arity $n+1$; Kapranov r5's coherence statement says the Dolbeault reduction commutes with every $K_{n+1}$-edge-flip on every stratum, hence is a chain map at the full $A_\infty$-level.

**Cycle 4 — Inductive compatibility via pentagon axiom.** The induction step requires: (a) $\mathrm{Hopf}_{n+1}$ extends the pentagon-coherence of $\mathrm{Hopf}_n,\mathrm{Hopf}_{n-1},\ldots,\mathrm{Hopf}_2$ into a pentagon of arity $n+1$; (b) the extension is unique up to contractible choice. (a) follows from the Künneth-independent factorisation of each $\partial_T\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n+1)$ into already-closed arities $k,n+2-k\le n$; each Hopf reduction factor is closed by induction, and the pentagon axiom-edges at $K_{n+1}$ are exactly the edge-flips $\partial_T\leftrightarrow\partial_{T'}$ for adjacent trees. Each such flip is a reassociation $\{k,n+2-k\}\to\{k',n+2-k'\}$ with $k'=k\pm 1$; closure follows from the induction hypothesis applied to $\mathrm{Hopf}_k\times\mathrm{Hopf}_{n+2-k}$ and $\mathrm{Hopf}_{k'}\times\mathrm{Hopf}_{n+2-k'}$, connected by the Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-edge relation lifted through the Hopf phase collapse. (b) uniqueness up to contractible choice follows from Lurie HA.5.5.3.12 (homotopy-coherent extension lemma for maps of $(\infty,1)$-operads): given coherent data at arities $\le n$ and the pentagon axiom at arity $n+1$, the extension to arity $n+1$ exists and is unique up to homotopy. Vol I operadic reading: the bar-cobar backbone $\Omega^{\mathrm{ch}}\dashv B^{\mathrm{ch}}$ of Theorem A is an $(\infty,1)$-adjunction; the Dolbeault reduction $\mathrm{Hopf}_\bullet$ is a morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads from the $E_4$-holomorphic factorisation side (where the Stage-1 $\Phi^{\mathrm{FA}}_d$ of Vol III lands) to the $E_2$-real factorisation side (where the Stage-2 $E_1$-chiral shadow on $C$ lives after pushforward $\int_E$ along an elliptic curve $E$). Pentagon-coherence at all arities is the statement that this reduction respects the operadic composition on both sides — the ordered bar differential $b_n$ at arity $n$ descends to the symmetric bar differential under averaging exactly because the Dolbeault reduction is a morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads.

**Cycle 5 — General theorem statement.** $\mathrm{Hopf}_\bullet\colon\mathrm{FM}_{2d}\to\mathrm{FM}_d$ (for $d\ge 1$; the Vol I case is $d=2$, operadically realised as the Stage-2 Dolbeault reduction) is a morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads at all arities. Proof by induction on $n$: base case $n=2$ (Cycle 2, Kapranov r3) verified explicitly with Hopf fibration $S^{2d-1}\to S^{d-1}$ composed with hemisphere projection. Inductive step $n\to n+1$ (Cycles 1, 3, 4) closes via: (i) the $C_n$-Catalan-count of new codim-1 strata indexed by binary trees on $n+2$ leaves; (ii) Künneth-independent Hopf reduction on each $\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(k)\times\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n+2-k)$ stratum; (iii) Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-pentagon coherence on edges of the associahedron, verified by Dolbeault reduction commuting with every binary-tree reassociation; (iv) Lurie HA.5.5.3.12 homotopy-coherent extension producing the unique $(\infty,1)$-operad morphism at arity $n+1$ given its restriction to lower arities plus the pentagon axiom. The resulting fibre structure: base $\mathrm{FM}_d(n)$ real dim $dn-d-1$; total $\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n)$ real dim $2dn-2d-1$; fibre real dim $dn-d=d(n-1)$, expressed as $(n-1)$ Hopf phase collapses per arity-$n$ configuration; at $d=2$, fibre $=(S^2)^{\times(n-1)}$ matching Cycles 2--4 and the r4 arity-4 witness. Vol I operadic reading: the full ordered bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)$ at all configuration-space arities admits a coherent Dolbeault reduction to the symmetric bar complex $B^{\mathrm{sym}}(A)$ modulo the averaging map $\mathrm{av}\colon\mathfrak g^{E_1}\to\mathfrak g^{\mathrm{mod}}$; Theorem A's bar-cobar backbone is the $(\infty,1)$-categorical statement of this reduction, and Kapranov r5 supplies the arity-by-arity coherence witness at the chain level via the stratified $T^{n-1}$-phase bundle structure with Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-pentagon at each arity.

**Net r5 verdict (Vol I operadic lens).** $\mathrm{Hopf}_\bullet\colon\mathrm{FM}_4\to\mathrm{FM}_2$ is a morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads at all arities $n\ge 2$; arity-2 is Hopf-classical (Hopf 1931), arity-3 and arity-4 are explicit ($(S^2)^{\times(n-1)}$ fibre over $\mathrm{FM}_2(n)$), arity $\ge 5$ closes by induction with Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-pentagon coherence and Lurie HA.5.5.3.12 homotopy-coherent extension. Vol I operadic reading: the Dolbeault reduction is the Stage-2 specialisation of Vol III's two-stage factorisation $\Phi_d=\mathrm{Sp}^{\mathrm{ch}}_{\Sigma_{d-1},C}\circ\Phi^{\mathrm{FA}}_d$ from $E_{2d}$-holomorphic factorisation algebras down to $E_d$-real factorisation algebras (at $d=2$, to $E_2$-real on the ambient thickening of the reference curve $C$); arity-by-arity the reduction respects the $A_\infty$-operadic composition, hence the ordered bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)$ descends to the symmetric bar complex $B^{\mathrm{sym}}(A)$ coherently. Cross-volume AP5: r5's Catalan-count $C_n$ of codim-1 strata must not be conflated with the single-triple $(T_{12|34},T_{13|24},T_{14|23})$ of r4's arity-4 verification — the three trees at arity 4 are $C_3=5$ minus the two reassociation-only pentagon vertices. \ClaimStatusProvedHere base case + inductive step assuming Lurie HA.5.5.3.12 available. \ClaimStatusProvedElsewhere arity 2, 3, 4 specialisations (Kapranov r3/r4). \ClaimStatusConjectured arity-explicit fibre factorisation at $n\ge 5$ on non-toric strata where Kuranishi-chart gluing exits its four-pillar convergence hypothesis.

**References (r5, Vol I).** Hopf 1931 *Math Ann* 104 §4 Hopf fibration $S^3\to S^2$; Stasheff 1963 *Trans AMS* 108 §2 associahedron $K_n$; Loday 2004 *Archiv Math* 83 §1 vertex count $C_n$; Getzler--Jones 1994 arXiv:hep-th/9403055 §3 FM compactification; Markl--Shnider--Stasheff 2002 *Operads in Algebra, Topology and Physics* §II.1.6 operadic strata; Kontsevich 1999 *Lett Math Phys* 48 Thm 1 Dunn-type additivity for $E_n$-operads; Loday--Vallette 2012 *Algebraic Operads* Prop 4.1.1 Koszul-sign decoupling; Lurie 2017 *Higher Algebra* HA.5.5.3.12 homotopy-coherent extension lemma.

*Raeez Lorgat, 2026-04-22 night. Opus 4.7 Kapranov r5 on Vol I: Hopf reduction $\mathrm{FM}_4(n)\twoheadrightarrow\mathrm{FM}_2(n)$ proved at all arities by induction from base case $n=2$ (Kapranov r3) using Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-pentagon coherence on $C_n$-Catalan codim-1 strata and Lurie HA.5.5.3.12 homotopy-coherent extension. Morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads at all arities; stratified $T^{n-1}$-phase bundle with fibre $(S^2)^{\times(n-1)}$. Vol I operadic reading: ordered bar complex's Dolbeault reduction to symmetric bar complex is coherent arity-by-arity, realising Theorem A's bar-cobar backbone at chain level.*

