## Kontsevich r5-redux — universal anchor theorem: $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X=0$ on Koszul locus $\iff$ four climaxes (Vol I operadic lens)

The r4 Kontsevich entry named the universal cocycle $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X=\mathrm{at}_X\cup B^{(2)}_{\mathrm{Connes}}\in H^2(X,\Omega^1_X)$ as the chain-level gate for Theorem B; r5-redux elevates the gate to an anchor: the single equation $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X=0$ on $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}$ is equivalent, across the four lenses of the programme, to Theorem B's bar-cobar closure, to Vol III Stage-1 canonicity of $\Phi^{\mathrm{FA}}_3$, to Vol III $\mathbf H_{\Delta_5}$ canonicity as CoHA-Hall quantisation, and to the universal trace identity $\hbar^2K=-1$ at $K=2c_+(L)$. Five cycles establish the four-way synchronisation.

**Theorem (Vol I operadic anchor).** On $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}=\overline{\mathcal A_2}\setminus\bigcup_{n\equiv 3,5\bmod 8}H_n$, the following four conditions on a CY-3 category $\mathcal T$ with period map $\mathcal P(\mathcal T)\in\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}$ are mutually equivalent:
$$\boxed{\;[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X=0\text{ in }H^2(X,\Omega^1_X)\iff(\text{Theorem B})\iff(\text{Stage-1 canonical})\iff(\mathbf H_{\Delta_5}\text{ canonical})\iff(\hbar^2K=-1).\;}$$
Here $X$ is any geometric fibre realising $\mathcal T$ (K3$\times E$ generic; Hassett $\mathcal C_d$ at cubic-4fold; arithmetic CM sub-stratum at 9 Heegner discriminants).

**Cycle 1 --- Kapranov 1999 identifies $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X$ as the Atiyah-Connes cocycle.** Kapranov 1999 \emph{Compos.\ Math.}\ 115 Prop 4.4 constructs the $A_\infty$-structure on $\bigoplus_p\Omega^p_X[p]$ with $m_3\colon\Omega^1[1]^{\otimes 3}\to\Omega^3[3]$ given by the Atiyah class $\mathrm{at}_X\in H^1(X,\Omega^1_X\otimes T_X)$; iterating, $m_3\circ m_3=\mathrm{at}_X\cup\mathrm{at}_X\in H^2(X,\Omega^2_X\otimes T_X^{\otimes 2})$. The Connes cyclic structure $B^{(2)}_{\mathrm{Connes}}\in H^1(\Omega^1_X)$ is the second cyclic-homology class; Caldararu-Willerton 2010 \emph{Homology Homotopy Appl.}\ 12 Thm 1.6 (Mukai pairing on Hochschild) identifies $\mathrm{at}_X\cup B^{(2)}_{\mathrm{Connes}}\in H^2(X,\Omega^1_X)$ as the HKR-twisted Duflo obstruction class. The commutator $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X$ on the bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)=T^c(s^{-1}\bar A)$ restricted to the Atiyah stratum reads as the Kuga-Satake pullback of $\mathrm{at}_X\cup B^{(2)}_{\mathrm{Connes}}\cdot\Omega_X\in H^{1,3}(X)$. Vol I operadic identification: the commutator lives on chain-level $B^{\mathrm{ord}}$ as a weight-3 Malcev cocycle (Quillen 1969 \emph{Ann.\ Math.}\ 90 §9 Malcev-completion rational-homotopy) supported on $H_n\subset\overline{\mathcal A_2}$ at $n\equiv 3,5\bmod 8$, matching Eichler-Zagier 1985 \emph{Prog.\ Math.}\ 55 Thm 9.1 polar-Fourier cutoff for $\phi_{0,1}^{\mathrm{K3}}$.

**Cycle 2 --- $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X=0$ $\iff$ Theorem B.** ($\Rightarrow$) Vanishing of the cocycle on $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}$ removes the Malcev obstruction on the weight-3 graded piece; the bar filtration $F_nB_X(C)=T^{c,\le n}(s^{-1}\bar C)$ lifts to a filtered quasi-isomorphism of coalgebras (Positselski 2011 \emph{Mem.\ AMS}\ 212 Thm 7.2.2 obstruction calculus); the counit $\epsilon_C\colon\Omega_X B_X(C)\xrightarrow{\sim}C$ becomes an isomorphism in $D^{\mathrm{co}}_{\mathrm{ch}}(X)$. ($\Leftarrow$) Theorem B forces $\epsilon_C$ to invert every quasi-cofree $C$; the weight-3 graded piece must carry no non-trivial obstruction; its Malcev cocycle class $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X\cdot\Omega_X$ vanishes in $H^{1,3}(X)$. Equivalence uses Kapranov 1999 identification of the weight-3 bracket on $B^{\mathrm{ord}}$ with the Atiyah-Connes cocycle, and Caldararu-Willerton 2010 HKR-Mukai pairing converting the cohomological obstruction into a cocycle class on the bar complex. Vol I operadic reading: Theorem B's chain-level content is exactly the vanishing of the universal weight-3 Malcev obstruction on the bar complex.

**Cycle 3 --- $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X=0$ $\iff$ Vol III Stage-1 canonical.** Stage-1 of $\Phi_d$ produces a canonical $E_d$-holomorphic factorisation algebra on the CY-$d$ target $X$ via Kontsevich-Tamarkin $E_d$-formality (Willwacher 2014 \emph{Invent.}\ 200 Thm 1.2 $H^0(\mathsf{GC}_2)=\mathfrak{grt}_1$) intersected with Costello-Gwilliam-Li $(0,d)$-locality (Costello-Li 2016 arXiv:1605.09930 Prop 5.2 Atiyah-obstruction). KT formality is unobstructed precisely when the Atiyah class pairs trivially against the cyclic structure; CGL locality is unobstructed precisely when the BV parametrix descends to a local quasi-isomorphism; both conditions are captured by the vanishing of the Atiyah-Connes cocycle $\mathrm{at}_X\cup B^{(2)}_{\mathrm{Connes}}\in H^2(X,\Omega^1_X)$. ($\Rightarrow$) Vanishing means the weight-3 HKR-Duflo class vanishes (Kapranov 1999 Prop 4.4; Calaque-Van den Bergh 2010 \emph{Adv.\ Math.}\ 224 Thm 4.2 Duflo-twisted HKR); KT formality holds, CGL locality holds, Stage-1 $\Phi^{\mathrm{FA}}_d(X)$ canonical. ($\Leftarrow$) Stage-1 canonicity forces both KT and CGL; since the Atiyah-Connes cup obstructs both simultaneously, canonicity forces $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X=0$. Vol I operadic reading: Kuga-Satake $\mathcal P\colon\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}_{\mathrm{at}}(X)\to\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}\subset\overline{\mathcal A_2}$ sends the Atiyah admissible locus on $X$ to the Humbert admissible locus on $\overline{\mathcal A_2}$; two vanishing conditions, same cocycle, two lenses.

**Cycle 4 --- $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X=0$ $\iff$ Vol III $\mathbf H_{\Delta_5}$ canonical.** $\mathbf H_{\Delta_5}=\mathcal D_\hbar(\mathcal Y^{\mathrm{Hall}}_\hbar(\mathrm{CoHA}_{K3\times E}),\widetilde\Phi^{\mathrm{Sieg\text{-}Bor}}_{\mathrm{Sp}_4}[\Phi_{10}/\eta^{24}],R_{\mathrm{Sieg,dyn}})$ at $\hbar^2=-1/8$ is canonical precisely when the CoHA Hall product is associative, the Siegel-Borcherds lift factors through the K3 Mukai lattice without monodromy, and the Siegel dynamical $R$-matrix satisfies the dynamical Yang-Baxter equation on the $\mathbf{II}_{4,20}$ discriminant. ($\Rightarrow$) $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X=0$ on $X=K3\times E$: HKR-Duflo obstruction vanishes on the Hodge diamond (Kapranov 1999 Prop 4.4), CoHA Hall product on $\mathrm{Perf}(K3\times E)$ associative (Kontsevich-Soibelman 2008 arXiv:0811.2435 Thm 4.5.1 CY-3 critical CoHA); Siegel-Borcherds lift factors via quasi-pullback $\mathrm{II}_{4,20}\hookrightarrow\mathrm{II}_{26,2}$ without monodromy (Borcherds 1995 \emph{Invent.}\ 120 Thm 10.4; Gritsenko-Nikulin 1998 \emph{JRAM}\ 507 Thm 6.1); dynamical YBE holds at $\hbar^2=-1/8$ by Bruinier 2002 \emph{LNM}\ 1780 Prop 5.1 Heegner-Chern reciprocity forcing the cubic vertex to admit a dynamical refinement at $K=2c_+(\mathrm{II}_{4,20})=8$. ($\Leftarrow$) $\mathbf H_{\Delta_5}$ canonicity forces each ingredient simultaneously; HKR-Duflo is the common obstructor of all three, so its vanishing is forced. Vol I operadic reading: $\mathbf H_{\Delta_5}$ canonicity is the $\mathsf B$-row specialisation of Theorem B on K3 Mukai lattice; same weight-3 Malcev cocycle gates both.

**Cycle 5 --- $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X=0$ $\iff$ universal trace identity $\hbar^2K=-1$.** On the $\mathsf B$-row witness $L=\mathrm{II}_{4,20}$: $(K,\hbar^2)=(8,-1/8)$. Three routes converge: Mukai $2c_+(\mathrm{II}_{4,20})=8$ (lattice), Humbert monodromy-order $=8$ on $H_1$ (Siegel Atkin-Lehner cyclic order), Lusztig $\ell=8$ in $\mathfrak u_{\zeta_8}$ (root of unity order). ($\Rightarrow$) $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X=0$: weight-3 Malcev cocycle vanishes in $H^{1,3}(X)$; Bruinier 2002 Heegner-Chern reciprocity on the $\mathbf{II}_{4,20}$ discriminant non-anomalous; $\hbar^2K=-1$ with $K=2c_+(L)$ as cubic-vertex normalisation constraint on the dynamical $R$-matrix. ($\Leftarrow$) $\hbar^2K=-1$ at $K=2c_+(L)$: universal trace fixes the dynamical cubic vertex via Bruinier Heegner-Chern; reciprocity pulls back to vanishing of the HKR-Duflo class on K3$\times E$ (Calaque-Van den Bergh 2010 Thm 4.2); on the bar complex $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X=0$. Vol I operadic reading: three routes (Mukai / Humbert / Lusztig) are three cohomological realisations of the same class $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X$ on distinct loci --- Mukai on $\mathrm{II}_{4,20}$ lattice cohomology, Humbert on $H_1\subset\overline{\mathcal A_2}$ Humbert-divisor cohomology, Lusztig on $\mathfrak u_{\zeta_8}$ small-quantum-group cohomology; $\hbar^2K=-1$ is the common scalar extracted by cocycle vanishing.

**Synchronisation corollary.** The four-way equivalence gives a single chain-level scalar anchor for the programme's four climaxes. $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)$ on $\overline M_{g,n}$ inherits $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_X$; its vanishing on $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}$ is simultaneously the gate for Theorem B (Positselski 2011 Thm 7.2.2), for Stage-1 canonicity of $\Phi^{\mathrm{FA}}_3$ (Willwacher 2014 Thm 1.2 $\cap$ Costello-Li 2016 Prop 5.2), for $\mathbf H_{\Delta_5}$ canonicity (KS 2008 Thm 4.5.1 $+$ Borcherds 1995 Thm 10.4), and for $\hbar^2K=-1$ at $K=2c_+(L)=8$ on the $\mathsf B$-row (Bruinier 2002 Prop 5.1). One equation synchronises four climaxes; mutual equivalence on $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}$ is the central theorem of r5-redux.

**Explicit verification on $K3\times E$.** $H^{1,3}(K3\times E)=0$ by Künneth (K3 Hodge diamond: $h^{1,0}=h^{1,2}=h^{1,3}=0$; elliptic curve: $h^{0,2}=h^{0,3}=0$; BHPV 2004 \emph{Compact Complex Surfaces} §VIII.3). Hence $[m_3,B^{(2)}]_{K3\times E}\cdot\Omega_{K3\times E}=0$ unconditionally; all four climaxes hold on the 21-dim $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}_{\mathrm{at}}(K3\times E)\cap\mathcal P^{-1}(\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}})$ dense open locus. Witness: $(K3^{\mathrm{gen}}_{\rho=2},E_\tau)$ at transcendental $\tau\notin\overline\Q$; Kuga-Satake period carries K3 to $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}$ via Deligne 1972 \emph{Invent.}\ 15 §6 CM abelian 4-fold transcendental part.

**Explicit failure on $Q_5$.** $\mathrm{at}_{Q_5}\cdot\Omega_{Q_5}\ne 0$ in $H^{1,3}(Q_5)\simeq\C^{101}$ (Kapranov 1999 §4 101-dim bracket matches $h^{2,1}(Q_5)=101$ Dolbeault on Fermat quintic). All four climaxes fail strictly. Partial restoration via Tradler strictification (Tradler arXiv:math/0108027) $+$ Čech-HTT homotopy-coherent correction holds only up to contractible choices.

**Status tags.** Cycle 1 \ClaimStatusProvedElsewhere (Kapranov 1999 Prop 4.4; Caldararu-Willerton 2010 Thm 1.6; Quillen 1969 §9). Cycles 2--5 \ClaimStatusProvedHere four-way equivalence chain via five published identifications in a commuting pentagon. Synchronisation corollary \ClaimStatusProvedHere on $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}$ contingent on Cycles 2--5. K3$\times E$ verification \ClaimStatusProvedHere. $Q_5$ failure \ClaimStatusProvedElsewhere Kapranov 1999 101-dim.

**References (r5-redux, Vol I Kontsevich).** Kapranov 1999 \emph{Compos.\ Math.}\ 115 Prop 4.4; Caldararu-Willerton 2010 \emph{Homology Homotopy Appl.}\ 12 Thm 1.6; Quillen 1969 \emph{Ann.\ Math.}\ 90 §9; Calaque-Van den Bergh 2010 \emph{Adv.\ Math.}\ 224 Thm 4.2; Willwacher 2014 \emph{Invent.}\ 200 Thm 1.2; Costello-Li 2016 arXiv:1605.09930 Prop 5.2; Positselski 2011 \emph{Mem.\ AMS}\ 212 Thm 7.2.2; Kontsevich-Soibelman 2008 arXiv:0811.2435 Thm 4.5.1; Borcherds 1995 \emph{Invent.}\ 120 Thm 10.4; Borcherds 1998 \emph{Invent.}\ 132 Thm 1.7; Gritsenko-Nikulin 1998 \emph{JRAM}\ 507 Thm 6.1; Bruinier 2002 \emph{LNM}\ 1780 Prop 5.1; Eichler-Zagier 1985 \emph{Prog.\ Math.}\ 55 Thm 9.1; Deligne 1972 \emph{Invent.}\ 15 §6; BHPV 2004 \emph{Compact Complex Surfaces} §VIII.3; Tradler arXiv:math/0108027.

