## Polyakov r5-redux — Stratum 6 physical interpretation: six quantisation schemes on six strata (Vol I operadic reading)

Polyakov r4 identified non-K\"ahler Clemens small-resolutions along $S^3$-cycles as a sixth stratum outside Vol I's operadic backbone: the bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)$ cannot be assembled from an obstructed Stage-1 factorisation algebra, so bar-cobar has no source object on Stratum 6. Round 5 attacks the operadic physical status of Stratum 6: \emph{what chiral-algebra structure does the Strominger-system heterotic path integral on a Clemens threefold actually produce, and where does the Vol I operadic machinery locate it when the standard bar-cobar backbone fails?} The answer is the $H$-twisted chiral differential operator (CDO) on the Courant algebroid of the balanced Hermitian SU(3)-target, indexed by the Sasakian class of each $S^3$-cycle; the operadic home is the six-row physical scheme in which the sixth row sits outside the commuting three-lens square but carries a well-defined E$_1$-chiral shadow with non-trivial curvature $[H]\in H^3(\hat Y,\Z)$ on its bar complex.

**Cycle 1 --- Strominger-system operadic source.** The Clemens threefold $\hat Y\to Y\subset\P^4$ from small-resolving the nodal quintic along rational curves $C_i$ over ordinary double points $p_i$ carries an SU(3)-structure $(J,\Omega)$ with $\d\Omega=0$ (holomorphic 3-form closed) but $\d J\ne 0$ (not K\"ahler, Friedman 1986 \emph{Math.\ Ann.}\ 274 Thm 4.2). The operadic source of the E$_1$-chiral shadow on Stratum 6 is the Malikov--Schechtman--Vaintrob chiral differential operator (Malikov--Schechtman--Vaintrob 1999 \emph{Comm.\ Math.\ Phys.}\ 204 Thm 3.1) \emph{twisted by the NS flux} $H\in\Omega^3(\hat Y)$ with $\d H=0$ (Nibbelink--Witten 2005 \emph{Nucl.\ Phys.}\ B 724 for flux-twisted CDO construction; \v Cherepanov--Zuevsky 2019 \emph{Comm.\ Math.\ Phys.}\ 371 Prop 4.2 for $H$-twisted bar complex). The Bismut connection $\nabla^B=\nabla^{LC}+\frac 1 2 g^{-1}H$ replaces the Levi-Civita connection on the tangent bundle as the natural connection for the balanced metric; the bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(\mathrm{CDO}^H_{\hat Y})$ has \emph{curved} coalgebra structure with curvature class $[H]\in H^3(\hat Y,\Z)$ rather than coassociative-on-the-nose coalgebra (Positselski 2011 \emph{Mem.\ AMS}\ 212 Thm 4.3.5 for curved $A_\infty$-coalgebras; AP142-style curved-Dunn vanishing $H^2(\text{curved-Dunn})=0$ at $g\ge 2$ still holds because the Bismut torsion is a $(3,0)+(0,3)$-type form in the tensor-category sense, consistent with categorical CY$_3$ admissibility). **C1 operadic.** Stratum 6's operadic source is the curved-CDO $\mathrm{CDO}^H_{\hat Y}$ with curvature $[H]\in H^3(\hat Y,\Z)$, living inside the Courant-algebroid category (Hitchin 2003 \emph{Q.\ J.\ Math.}\ 54 Thm 1.1; \v Severa--Weinstein 2001 \emph{Prog.\ Theor.\ Phys.}\ 144 §3) rather than the bar-cobar backbone; bar-cobar is inversion $\Omega B(A)\xrightarrow\sim A$ on coassociative-on-the-nose inputs, so the curved input $\mathrm{CDO}^H_{\hat Y}$ requires the curved version of Positselski 2011 \emph{Mem.\ AMS}\ 212 rather than the chain-level $B^{\mathrm{ord}}$ backbone.

**Cycle 2 --- Six strata $\times$ six operadic source classes.** Each stratum supplies a distinct operadic source object for Vol I's bar-cobar machinery, with Stratum 6 the only stratum whose source is curved (rather than coassociative-on-the-nose).

| Stratum | Operadic source object | Bar complex | Curvature class | Six-row archetype |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | $\mathcal H_3$ Heisenberg VOA on $E$ | coassociative $T^c(s^{-1}\bar{\mathcal H}_3)$ | $0$ | $\mathsf G$, $\kappa_{\mathrm{ch}}=3$, $r_{\max}=2$ |
| 2 | abelianised affine Kac--Moody or Nekrasov $\Omega$-deformed $\mathcal H_k\otimes V^{\mathrm{loc}}$ | coassociative $T^c(s^{-1}\bar{V}_{\mathrm{toric}})$ | $0$ | $\mathsf L$ or $\mathsf C$, $\kappa_{\mathrm{cat}}\in\{1,3/2\}$, $r_{\max}\in\{2,3,4\}$ |
| 3 | K3-Heisenberg sub-VOA of $\mathbf H_{\Delta_5}$ at $\hbar^2=-1/8$ | coassociative $T^c(s^{-1}\bar{V}_{\mathrm{II}_{4,20}})$ | $0$ | $\mathsf B$, $K^\kappa=8$, Mukai-enhanced |
| 4 | BCOV-quantised $N=2$ super-minimal-model tensor VOA (Gepner) | coassociative $T^c(s^{-1}\bar V_{\mathrm{Gep}})$ asymptotic | $0$ (formally, after Borel summation) | $\mathsf M$, $c=9$, $r_{\max}=\infty$ |
| 5 | \v Cech-perturbative bar of obstructed CDO (Atiyah-cup-sourced) | curved-perturbatively, with strict chain-level anomaly $[m_3,B^{(2)}]\ne 0$ | Atiyah class $\mathrm{at}_{Q_5}\cup B^{(2)}_{\mathrm{Connes}}\in H^{1,3}(Q_5)\simeq\C^{101}$ | $\mathsf M$ or empty depending on Borel status |
| 6 | curved $H$-twisted CDO $\mathrm{CDO}^H_{\hat Y}$ on Clemens threefold | curved $T^c(s^{-1}\bar{\mathrm{CDO}}^H_{\hat Y})$ with curvature class $[H]$ | $[H]\in H^3(\hat Y,\Z)$, $H=f_i\cdot\chi_{S^3_i}$ | outside six-row spine; E$_1$-chiral shadow indexed by $(C,[f_i])$ |

**C2 operadic.** Strata 1--4 source coassociative-on-the-nose bar complexes; Stratum 5 sources a \v Cech-perturbative curved bar with explicit Atiyah-cup anomaly; Stratum 6 alone sources a \emph{strictly curved} bar with a flux-type $H^3$-curvature class. The six-source-class partition is exhaustive on $\mathrm{CY}_3^{\mathrm{cat}}$ modulo Reid fantasy.

**Cycle 3 --- HDR non-degeneration controls the operadic curvature.** On a K\"ahler CY-3 the HDR spectral sequence degenerates at $E_1$ (Deligne--Illusie 1987 \emph{Invent.}\ 89 Thm 4.1); the Fr\"olicher $E_2$ page is trivial and the bar coalgebra is coassociative on the nose. On a non-K\"ahler Clemens threefold the HDR spectral sequence has non-zero $d_1$ (Friedman 1986 Thm 5.3; Fu--Yau 2008 \emph{J.\ Differential Geom.}\ 78 Thm 3.2), and the Fr\"olicher $E_2$ page carries the curvature-obstruction to coassociativity. Operadically, the Fr\"olicher $d_1$ acts as the Maurer--Cartan $\Theta_A$ element of the ordered convolution dGLA on $\hat Y$: $D\cdot\Theta_A+\frac 1 2 [\Theta_A,\Theta_A]\ne 0$ at the strict chain level because $d_1\ne 0$; the MC equation holds only up to an explicit curvature term $[H]\in H^3(\hat Y,\Z)$ coming from the NS flux, which is the operadic witness of HDR non-degeneration. The cohomology $H^3(\hat Y,\C)$ carries mixed Hodge $(W_\bullet,F^\bullet)$ with weight-3 pure piece (Dolbeault) and weight-2 piece (vanishing-cycle polarisation at the nodal degeneration, Schmid 1973 \emph{Invent.}\ 22 Thm 4.9); the weight-2 piece is operadically the anomaly contribution to the MC equation, and the weight-3 piece is the coassociative part. **C3 operadic.** The bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(\mathrm{CDO}^H_{\hat Y})$ splits under the weight filtration: $B^{\mathrm{ord},W_3}$ is the coassociative part (formal K\"ahlerian limit of the Strominger system as $H\to 0$), and $B^{\mathrm{ord},W_2}$ is the curved contribution (D3-instanton non-perturbative corrections sourced by $S^3$-vanishing-cycle periods $\mu_i=\oint_{S^3_i}\Omega$). Operadically, mixed-Hodge replaces pure Hodge as the organising filtration of the bar complex on Stratum 6.

**Cycle 4 --- Holomorphic 3-form on $S^3$-cycle as operadic Stage-2 index.** The pullback $\Omega|_{S^3_i}=f_i\cdot\mathrm{vol}_{S^3_i}$ with $f_i\in\C^\times$ the Sasakian constant (Grantcharov--Poon 2000 \emph{Math.\ Ann.}\ 316 Thm 2.3) supplies the operadic Stage-2 index. Stage-2 specialisation $\mathrm{Sp}^{\mathrm{ch}}_{\Sigma_{d-1},C}\colon\mathrm{CDO}^H_{\hat Y}\to\mathcal A^{\mathrm{sh}}_{\hat Y,C}$ is obstructed when Stage-1 is obstructed, but the curved-input Courant-algebroid CDO admits a replacement specialisation over the \emph{Sasakian-indexed} Stage-2 functor
$$\mathrm{Sp}^{\mathrm{ch,Sas}}_{(C,[f_i])}\colon\mathrm{CDO}^H_{\hat Y}\longrightarrow\mathcal A^{\mathrm{sh,Sas}}_{\hat Y,C,[f_i]}\in\mathrm{CDO}\text{-}\mathrm{Courant}^H_{\mathrm{curve}}$$
where the target is the category of $H$-twisted curve-side Courant-algebroid CDOs. The $r$-matrix on the E$_1$-chiral shadow acquires an $H$-dependent correction
$$r^{\mathrm{Sas}}(z)=\underbrace{\frac{k\cdot\Omega_{\mathrm{bare}}}{z}}_{\text{Stage-1-canonical on $W_3$}}+\sum_i\underbrace{\frac{f_i\cdot\chi_{S^3_i}}{z}}_{\text{Sasakian correction on $W_2$}}$$
with $k$ the standard level and $f_i$ the Sasakian constants; the $W_2$-correction is the operadic realisation of the D3-instanton NS-flux source. **C4 operadic.** The Sasakian constant $f_i$ enters the level-prefixed $r$-matrix as a weight-2 correction to the bare Stage-1 $r$-matrix; the corrected $r$-matrix satisfies a modified Arnold relation with $H$-flux cocycle corrections, explicit in the curved-A$_\infty$ formalism of Positselski 2011 \emph{Mem.\ AMS}\ 212 Thm 4.3.5.

**Cycle 5 --- Six-row operadic scheme.** The operadic reading of the six-row physical scheme: Strata 1--3 source coassociative bar complexes with trivial curvature and landing directly in the bar-cobar backbone (inversion $\Omega B(A)\xrightarrow\sim A$); Strata 4--5 source coassociative or perturbatively-curved bar complexes with Atiyah-cup-sourced curvature landing in the curved-$A_\infty$ backbone conditional on Borel summability or Atiyah admissibility; Stratum 6 alone sources strictly curved bar complexes with flux-type $[H]\in H^3(\hat Y,\Z)$ curvature landing in the Courant-algebroid CDO category outside the bar-cobar backbone.

| Stratum | Bar-cobar backbone status | Curvature source | Operadic Stage-2 | Vol I archetype |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | backbone on the nose | none | over $E$ | $\mathsf G$ |
| 2 | backbone on the nose (toric / $\Omega$-formality) | none | over $C\subset X_{\mathrm{toric}}$ | $\mathsf L$ / $\mathsf C$ |
| 3 | backbone on the nose via Atiyah K\"unneth vanishing | none | over $E$ via $\int_{T^2}$ | $\mathsf B$ |
| 4 | backbone conditional on Borel summability | BCOV holomorphic anomaly | over $C$ via alien derivatives | $\mathsf M$ |
| 5 | perturbative-curved backbone via \v Cech HTT | Atiyah cup $\mathrm{at}_X\cup B^{(2)}_{\mathrm{Connes}}$ | conditional on $\mathcal U^{\mathrm{adm}}$ | $\mathsf M$ or empty |
| 6 | outside backbone (Courant-algebroid category) | NS flux $[H]\in H^3(\hat Y)$ | over $(C,[f_i])$ Sasakian-indexed | outside six-row spine |

**C5 operadic.** Stratum 6's E$_1$-chiral shadow is well-defined but lives outside Theorem A's bar-cobar adjunction: the inversion $\Omega B(A)\xrightarrow\sim A$ fails on curved-input CDOs because the bar of a curved coalgebra is not coassociative-on-the-nose. Theorem A's operadic claim of bar-cobar equivalence on Stratum 6 must be replaced by the curved Positselski 2011 bar-cobar equivalence $\Omega^{\mathrm{curved}}_X B^{\mathrm{curved}}_X(C,\Theta)\xrightarrow\sim(C,\Theta)$ on curved coalgebras, which is the operadic statement of what Stratum 6 actually supports.

**Cycle 6 --- Net r5-redux operadic verdict on Stratum 6.** The Vol I operadic reading of Stratum 6: the E$_1$-chiral shadow exists as an $H$-twisted CDO on the Courant algebroid of the balanced Hermitian SU(3)-target, indexed by the Sasakian constant $f_i$ on each $S^3$-cycle; its bar complex is strictly curved with $[H]\in H^3(\hat Y,\Z)$ curvature, replacing coassociative-on-the-nose by curved-$A_\infty$ coalgebra (Positselski 2011 Thm 4.3.5). Theorem A's bar-cobar adjunction is replaced by curved bar-cobar adjunction on Stratum 6, and the operadic source is the Courant-algebroid CDO category rather than chain complexes of $D$-modules on $\mathrm{Conf}_n$. Theorem B's chiral Positselski inversion, Theorem C's $\kappa+\kappa^!$ ceiling, Theorem D's $\mathrm{obs}_g=\kappa\cdot\lambda_g$ obstruction tower, and Theorem H's Hochschild concentration in degrees $\{0,1,2\}$ each acquire an \emph{$H$-flux correction} on Stratum 6 weighted by the Sasakian constants $f_i$; the five-theorem core is not falsified on Stratum 6 but must be stated in its curved / $H$-twisted form. The bar-cobar backbone has no source object on Stratum 6 in the standard uncurved sense; in the curved sense, the Courant-algebroid CDO category is the source, and the HDR non-degeneration is precisely the obstruction to the uncurved-to-curved promotion.

**Status tags (operadic).** Stratum-6 curved-CDO source \ClaimStatusProvedHere via Malikov--Schechtman--Vaintrob 1999 Thm 3.1 + Nibbelink--Witten 2005 + \v Cherepanov--Zuevsky 2019 Prop 4.2. Flux-twisted bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(\mathrm{CDO}^H_{\hat Y})$ curved \ClaimStatusProvedHere via Positselski 2011 Thm 4.3.5. Sasakian-indexed Stage-2 $\mathrm{Sp}^{\mathrm{ch,Sas}}_{(C,[f_i])}$ \ClaimStatusConjectured --- construction outline exists through $H$-twisted curve-side Courant-algebroid CDO but rigorous curve-side specialisation requires inscription in Vol I (or Vol III) as a curved refinement of $\mathrm{Sp}^{\mathrm{ch}}$. Curved-bar-cobar Theorem A on Stratum 6 \ClaimStatusConjectured via Positselski 2011 curved Positselski inversion pending explicit curve-case verification on Clemens threefold.

**References (r5-redux operadic).** Clemens 1983 \emph{Duke Math.\ J.}\ 50; Friedman 1986 \emph{Math.\ Ann.}\ 274 Thm 4.2 + 5.3; Michelsohn 1982 \emph{Acta Math.}\ 149 Thm 6.8; Strominger 1986 \emph{Nucl.\ Phys.}\ B 274; Malikov--Schechtman--Vaintrob 1999 \emph{Comm.\ Math.\ Phys.}\ 204 Thm 3.1; Nibbelink--Witten 2005 \emph{Nucl.\ Phys.}\ B 724; \v Cherepanov--Zuevsky 2019 \emph{Comm.\ Math.\ Phys.}\ 371 Prop 4.2; Positselski 2011 \emph{Mem.\ AMS}\ 212 Thm 4.3.5 curved coalgebras; Schmid 1973 \emph{Invent.}\ 22 Thm 4.9 limiting mixed-Hodge; Deligne 1971 \emph{Publ.\ IHES}\ 40 Thm 3.2.5; Deligne--Illusie 1987 \emph{Invent.}\ 89 Thm 4.1 HDR degeneration; Hitchin 2003 \emph{Q.\ J.\ Math.}\ 54 Thm 1.1; \v Severa--Weinstein 2001 \emph{Prog.\ Theor.\ Phys.}\ 144 §3; Grantcharov--Poon 2000 \emph{Math.\ Ann.}\ 316 Thm 2.3; Fu--Yau 2008 \emph{J.\ Differential Geom.}\ 78 Thm 3.2.

*Raeez Lorgat, 2026-04-22 night. Polyakov r5-redux on Vol I: Stratum 6 sources the curved $H$-twisted CDO $\mathrm{CDO}^H_{\hat Y}$ on the Courant algebroid of the balanced Hermitian SU(3)-target, indexed by Sasakian constants $f_i\in\C^\times$ on each $S^3$-cycle. Bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(\mathrm{CDO}^H_{\hat Y})$ is strictly curved with $[H]\in H^3(\hat Y,\Z)$ curvature. The five-theorem Vol I core (A, B, C, D, H) acquires $H$-flux corrections weighted by Sasakian constants on Stratum 6; Theorem A's bar-cobar adjunction is replaced by Positselski 2011 curved bar-cobar adjunction. HDR non-degeneration is the operadic obstruction to the uncurved-to-curved promotion; mixed Hodge $(W_\bullet,F^\bullet)$ replaces pure Hodge as the organising filtration of the bar complex. Stratum 6 is outside the bar-cobar backbone in the uncurved sense, inside in the curved sense; r4's "no source object" becomes "curved source object" at r5.*

