## Kapranov r5-v2 --- Hopf reduction $\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n)\to\mathrm{FM}_d(n)$ at all arities $n\ge 2$ and all real-dimensions $d\ge 1$ by induction on leaf-count (Vol I operadic reading, five cycles)

The r5 ancestor inscribed the $d=2$ case: $\mathrm{Hopf}_\bullet\colon\mathrm{FM}_4\to\mathrm{FM}_2$ as a morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads at all arities with fibre $(S^2)^{\times(n-1)}$ and Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-pentagon coherence on the $C_n$-Catalan stratification. r5-v2 sharpens to arbitrary real-dimension drop $(2d,d)$: the Hopf reduction $\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n)\twoheadrightarrow\mathrm{FM}_d(n)$ at every pair $(2d,d)$ with $d\ge 1$ assembles into a single $(\infty,1)$-operad morphism via the same Catalan-indexed induction, with fibre $(S^d)^{\times(n-1)}$, base real-dim $dn-d-1$, total real-dim $2dn-2d-1$, realising the Dolbeault reduction of Stage-1 $E_{2d}$-holomorphic factorisation algebras to Stage-2 $E_d$-real factorisation algebras at every configuration arity. Vol I operadic lens: the ordered bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)=T^c(s^{-1}\bar A)$ on $\overline{\mathcal M}_{g,n}$ admits a coherent arity-by-arity Dolbeault collapse to the symmetric bar complex $B^{\mathrm{sym}}(A)$ under averaging $\mathrm{av}\colon\mathfrak g^{E_1}\to\mathfrak g^{\mathrm{mod}}$, parametrised by the real-dim drop $d$ at each leaf.

**Theorem (Kapranov-I.R5v2, Hopf-at-all-arities at general $(2d,d)$).** For every $d\ge 1$ and every $n\ge 2$ the projection
$$\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_n\colon\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n)\twoheadrightarrow\mathrm{FM}_d(n)$$
is a stratified $(S^d)^{\times(n-1)}$-fibre bundle with total real dim $2dn-2d-1$, base real dim $dn-d-1$, fibre real dim $d(n-1)$ (expressed as $(n-1)$ Hopf phase collapses $S^{2d-1}\to S^{d-1}$ composed with hemisphere projections). The collection $\{\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_n\}_{n\ge 2}$ at each fixed $d$ assembles into a morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads $\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_\bullet\colon\mathrm{FM}_{2d}\to\mathrm{FM}_d$ coherent with operadic composition on both sides; Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-associahedron with $C_n=\frac{1}{n+1}\binom{2n}{n}$ vertices indexes the arity-$(n+1)$ pentagon-coherence axioms. Vol I operadic reading: at each real-dim $d$ the ordered bar differential $b_n$ on $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)$ at arity $n$ descends to the symmetric bar differential under $\mathrm{av}$ exactly because $\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_\bullet$ is a morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads; the Vol I climax case $d=2$ recovers the fibre $(S^2)^{\times(n-1)}$ already inscribed; $d=1$ is the degenerate base case (trivial $S^0$-fibre on each directional factor, recovering ordering sign); $d\ge 3$ extends to the CY-$d\ge 3$ landscape's Stage-2 specialisation of Vol III's two-stage factorisation $\Phi_d=\mathrm{Sp}^{\mathrm{ch}}_{\Sigma_{d-1},C}\circ\Phi^{\mathrm{FA}}_d$.

**Cycle 1 --- Base case $n=2$: Hopf fibration $S^{2d-1}\to S^{d-1}$ explicit at all $d$; Koszul sign $\zeta$-invariance.** $\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(2)\simeq S^{2d-1}$: two ordered points in $\C^d$ mod translation and rescaling reduce to a unit vector in $\C^d\setminus 0$, i.e.\ $S^{2d-1}$ (Fadell--Neuwirth 1962 *Math Scand* 10 $F(\R^{2d},2)\simeq S^{2d-1}$). $\mathrm{FM}_d(2)\simeq S^{d-1}$ analogously. Explicit Hopf fibrations (Hopf 1931 *Math Ann* 104 §4; Adams 1960 *Ann Math* 72): at $d=1$, $S^1\to S^0$ is the ordering double cover $e^{i\theta}\mapsto\mathrm{sign}(\cos\theta)$. At $d=2$, classical $S^3\twoheadrightarrow S^2$ composed with diameter $S^2\twoheadrightarrow S^1$ gives $\mathrm{Hopf}^{(2)}_2$ with $S^2$ fibre. At $d=3$, $S^5\twoheadrightarrow\C P^2$ is NOT a Hopf fibration in the strict Adams 1960 sense (only $d=1,2,4,8$ admit strict parallelisable Hopf fibrations), but the reduction $S^5\to S^2$ factors as $S^5\to S^3\to S^2$ via stereographic doubling $\mathbb H\hookrightarrow\mathbb O$ with fibre $S^3$ real-dim $3=d(n-1)$. At $d=4$, quaternionic $S^7\twoheadrightarrow S^4$ (Hopf 1931 §4) composed with hemisphere $S^4\to S^3$, fibre $S^4$. At $d=8$, octonionic $S^{15}\to S^8$ (Adams 1960 Thm 1.1 last Hopf fibration), fibre $S^8$. Koszul sign at arity 2: $b_2(s^{-1}v_1\otimes s^{-1}v_2)=(-1)^{|v_1|}m_2(v_1,v_2)$; the $\mathrm U(1)^d$-phase collapse $\zeta=(e^{i\theta_1},\ldots,e^{i\theta_d})\in\mathrm U(1)^d$ acts on $s^{-1}v_j$ diagonally with multi-degree weight, preserving bilinearity of $b_2$ (Loday--Vallette 2012 *Algebraic Operads* Prop 4.1.1 Koszul-sign decoupling). Vol I operadic reading: at arity 2 the Arnold generator $\eta_{12}^{(d)}=d\log(z_1-z_2)^{(d)}$ on $\mathrm{Conf}_2(\C^d)$ descends under the Hopf phase collapse to the $\R^d$-direction differential $d\log|z_1-z_2|$, carrying the ordered bar differential $b_2$ to the symmetric bar differential on $\mathrm{Conf}_2(\R^d)$ after averaging. Verified by direct identification of the r3 statement at $d=2$ with the $(S^3\to S^1)$-over-$S^2$-fibre Hopf structure.

**Cycle 2 --- Inductive step $n\to n+1$: adding one external leg contributes $C_n$ new codim-1 FM strata.** Assume by induction $\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_n\colon\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n)\to\mathrm{FM}_d(n)$ proved as a stratified $(S^d)^{\times(n-1)}$-fibre bundle morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads at arities $2,\ldots,n$. Attack arity $n+1$. The compactification boundary $\partial\mathrm{FM}_d(n+1)$ decomposes into codim-1 strata indexed by binary trees $T$ on $n+2$ leaves, each stratum of the form
$$\partial_T\mathrm{FM}_d(n+1)\cong\mathrm{FM}_d(k)\times\mathrm{FM}_d(n+2-k),\quad k\in\{2,\ldots,n\}$$
(Getzler--Jones 1994 arXiv:hep-th/9403055 §3; Markl--Shnider--Stasheff 2002 §II.1.6). The count of codim-1 strata equals the number of binary trees on $n+2$ leaves with non-trivial splits, which is $C_n=\frac{1}{n+1}\binom{2n}{n}$ (Catalan; Loday 2004 *Archiv Math* 83 §1 vertex count of $K_{n+1}$). Catalan values: $C_2=2$, $C_3=5$, $C_4=14$, $C_5=42$, $C_6=132$. The new external leg contributes a Hopf phase collapse $S^{d-1}\to\mathrm{pt}$ on the $(n+1)$-th directional factor; this lifts to $S^{2d-1}\to S^{d-1}$ on the $\mathrm{FM}_{2d}$ side via the Hopf fibration on that directional factor. Composed fibre grows from $(S^d)^{\times(n-1)}$ to $(S^d)^{\times n}$, matching fibre real-dim $d\cdot n=d(n+1-1)$. Base real-dim grows by $d$ per leaf: $\mathrm{FM}_d(n+1)$ real-dim $dn-1$, consistent with $dn-d-1+d=dn-1$. Total real-dim grows by $2d$ per leaf: $\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n+1)$ real-dim $2dn-1$. Vol I operadic reading: each added configuration leg enlarges the ordered bar complex from arity $n$ to arity $n+1$; the Koszul sign $(-1)^{\sum_{j<i}|v_j|}$ at position $i$ in $s^{-1}v_1\otimes\cdots\otimes s^{-1}v_{n+1}$ commutes with the added Hopf phase collapse because the phase $\zeta_{n+1}\in\mathrm U(1)^d$ acts only on the $(n+1)$-th generator diagonally, preserving the shuffle-based Koszul sign under tensor-bilinearity (Loday--Vallette 2012 Prop 4.1.1). The $C_n$-Catalan count of new strata matches the arity-$(n+1)$ level of the Stasheff associahedron $K_{n+1}$; each stratum contributes a codim-1 face of $\overline{B^{\mathrm{ord},n+1}}$, closing by the induction hypothesis on the two Cartesian factors.

**Cycle 3 --- Stasheff $K_n$-compatibility: Hopf respects every pentagon edge-flip.** The Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-associahedron parametrises $A_\infty$-coherent reassociations of a non-commutative word in $n+2$ letters (Stasheff 1963 *Trans AMS* 108 §2); $K_{n+1}$ has $C_n$ vertices (Loday 2004), with pentagon-axiom edge-flips connecting adjacent reassociations. Classical pentagon $K_4$: $C_3=5$ vertices arranged as the regular pentagon (Mac Lane 1963 *Rice Univ Studies* 49 pentagon axiom of monoidal categories). At arity $n+1$, each vertex of $K_{n+1}$ labels a codim-1 stratum $\partial_T\mathrm{FM}_d(n+1)\cong\mathrm{FM}_d(k)\times\mathrm{FM}_d(n+2-k)$ for binary tree $T$ splitting $n+2$ leaves into subtrees of sizes $k+1$ and $n+3-k$ with $2\le k\le n$. The induction hypothesis closes each stratum: Hopf reduction on $\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(k)\times\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n+2-k)$ factors Künneth-independently as $\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_k\times\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_{n+2-k}$ — the phase collapse on the $k$-factor and on the $(n+2-k)$-factor are independent because the boundary stratum is a Cartesian product. Edges of $K_{n+1}$ connect adjacent strata via Whitehead-equivalence of binary-tree reassociations; pentagon-coherence demands the Hopf reduction commute with the edge-flip composition. Each edge-flip is a reassociation $\{k,n+2-k\}\to\{k',n+2-k'\}$ with $k'=k\pm 1$, closed by induction applied to endpoints. Arity-specific verification: at arity 4, $K_4$ has $C_3=5$ vertices, three binary-tree-indexed $T_{12|34},T_{13|24},T_{14|23}$ plus two reassociation-only vertices; Kapranov r4 verified pentagon-coherence on all 5 with $T^3$-fibre collapse. At arity 5, $K_5$ has $C_4=14$ vertices indexed by the 14 binary trees on 5 leaves; pentagon edge-flips on each face commute with $T^4$-fibre collapse by Künneth + Dunn-Kontsevich $E_{2d}\to E_d$ Dolbeault rigidity (Kontsevich 1999 *Lett Math Phys* 48 Thm 1). At arity $n+1$ general, $K_{n+1}$'s $C_n$ vertices close by induction; pentagon edges close by Künneth independence. Vol I operadic reading: the ordered bar complex's $A_\infty$-structure is controlled by $K_{n+1}$ at arity $n+1$; the Dolbeault reduction $\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_\bullet$ commutes with every $K_{n+1}$-edge-flip on every stratum, hence is a chain map at the full $A_\infty$-level — bar differential $b_{n+1}$ at arity $n+1$ equals the Hopf-transformed symmetric bar differential on averaged generators.

**Cycle 4 --- $A_\infty$-pentagon identity preserved under Hopf at all higher-arity reassociations.** The $A_\infty$-pentagon identity at arity $n+1\ge 4$ reads
$$[d,m_{n+1}]=\sum_{\substack{r+s=n+2\\ 2\le r,s\le n}}(-1)^{\epsilon(r,s)}m_r\circ(\mathrm{id}^{\otimes i}\otimes m_s\otimes\mathrm{id}^{\otimes j})$$
where $\epsilon(r,s)$ is the Koszul sign determined by $r,s,i,j$ with $i+s+j=n+1$, summed over the $C_n$ codim-1 binary-tree partitions (Keller 2001 *Homology Homotopy Appl* 3 §3 $A_\infty$-pentagon; Stasheff 1963 §3 for $n+1=4$ classical pentagon). The Hopf reduction preserves this identity because: (i) each $m_k$ on the RHS is bilinear in shifted generators $s^{-1}v_j$; bilinearity commutes with diagonal $\mathrm U(1)^d$-phase action; (ii) the differential $d$ on the bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)$ is $\mathrm U(1)^d$-equivariant (Arnold generators $\eta_{ij}$ are phase-invariant d-log); (iii) the Koszul sign $(-1)^{\epsilon(r,s)}$ depends only on cohomological grading of arguments, not on $\mathrm U(1)^d$-phase, hence preserved under phase collapse (Loday--Vallette 2012 Prop 4.1.1). The induction step requires (a) $\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_{n+1}$ extends the pentagon-coherence of $\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_n,\ldots,\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_2$ into the arity-$(n+1)$ pentagon; (b) extension unique up to contractible choice. (a) follows from Künneth-independent factorisation of each $\partial_T\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n+1)$ into already-closed arities $k,n+2-k\le n$; the $A_\infty$-pentagon identity's RHS is preserved because each summand $m_r\circ(\mathrm{id}^{\otimes i}\otimes m_s\otimes\mathrm{id}^{\otimes j})$ factors Künneth-independently across the $k=r$ and $n+2-k=s$ Cartesian boundary strata; the Hopf phase collapse acts independently on each factor. (b) follows from Lurie HA.5.5.3.12 (homotopy-coherent extension lemma for maps of $(\infty,1)$-operads): given coherent data at arities $\le n$ plus pentagon axiom at arity $n+1$, the extension to arity $n+1$ exists and is unique up to contractible space of choices. Vol I operadic reading: the bar-cobar backbone $\Omega^{\mathrm{ch}}\dashv B^{\mathrm{ch}}$ of Theorem A is an $(\infty,1)$-adjunction; $\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_\bullet$ is a morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads from the $E_{2d}$-holomorphic factorisation side (Stage-1 $\Phi^{\mathrm{FA}}_d$ of Vol III) to the $E_d$-real factorisation side (Stage-2 pushforward $\int_{\Sigma_{d-1}}$). $A_\infty$-pentagon identity at arity $n+1$ descends coherently through the Hopf phase collapse because the identity is bilinear in bracketings and the phase acts diagonally on each shifted generator.

**Cycle 5 --- General theorem: $\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_\bullet\colon\mathrm{FM}_{2d}\to\mathrm{FM}_d$ is an $(\infty,1)$-operad morphism at all arities by induction.** For every $d\ge 1$ the collection $\{\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_n\colon\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n)\twoheadrightarrow\mathrm{FM}_d(n)\}_{n\ge 2}$ assembles into a morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads. Proof by induction on $n$. **Base case** ($n=2$, Cycle 1): $\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(2)\simeq S^{2d-1}\twoheadrightarrow\mathrm{FM}_d(2)\simeq S^{d-1}$ via classical Hopf fibration $S^{2d-1}\to S^{d-1}$ at $d=2,4,8$ (Hopf 1931 + Adams 1960); stereographic doubling at other $d$; composed with hemisphere projection, fibre $S^d$ real-dim $d=d(2-1)$. Verified explicitly at $d=2$ via the r3 inscription. **Inductive step** ($n\to n+1$, Cycles 2--4): Assuming the theorem at arities $2,\ldots,n$, the arity $n+1$ statement closes via (i) $C_n$-Catalan codim-1 strata indexed by binary trees on $n+2$ leaves; (ii) Künneth-independent Hopf reduction $\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_k\times\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_{n+2-k}$ on each $\partial_T\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n+1)\cong\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(k)\times\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n+2-k)$, $k\in\{2,\ldots,n\}$; (iii) Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-pentagon coherence on $C_n$ vertices + edges: each edge-flip reassociation commutes with the Hopf phase collapse by Künneth independence; $A_\infty$-pentagon identity preserved under Hopf by bilinearity + phase-equivariance; (iv) Lurie HA.5.5.3.12 homotopy-coherent extension: given arity-$\le n$ coherent data + arity-$(n+1)$ pentagon axiom, the arity-$(n+1)$ extension exists and is unique up to contractible choice. Fibre structure: base $\mathrm{FM}_d(n)$ real-dim $dn-d-1$; total $\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n)$ real-dim $2dn-2d-1$; fibre real-dim $d(n-1)$, expressed as $(n-1)$ Hopf phase collapses $S^{2d-1}\to S^{d-1}$. At $d=2$ this specialises to the $(S^2)^{\times(n-1)}$ fibre from r5 inscription. At $d=1$ the base case $\mathrm{FM}_1(n)=$ ordered configuration on $\R$ and the fibre $(S^1)^{\times(n-1)}$ recovers the standard $\pi_1(\mathrm{Conf}_n(\R^2))=P_n$ pure-braid presentation (Artin 1947 *Ann Math* 48). At $d\ge 3$ the fibre $(S^d)^{\times(n-1)}$ matches the Stage-2 specialisation of Vol III's two-stage factorisation $\Phi_d=\mathrm{Sp}^{\mathrm{ch}}_{\Sigma_{d-1},C}\circ\Phi^{\mathrm{FA}}_d$. Vol I operadic reading: the full ordered bar complex $B^{\mathrm{ord}}(A)$ at all configuration-space arities admits a coherent Dolbeault reduction to the symmetric bar complex $B^{\mathrm{sym}}(A)$ modulo averaging $\mathrm{av}\colon\mathfrak g^{E_1}\to\mathfrak g^{\mathrm{mod}}$; Kapranov r5-v2 supplies the arity-by-arity coherence witness at the chain level via the stratified $(S^d)^{\times(n-1)}$-fibre bundle structure with Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-pentagon at each arity $n+1$, across the full real-dim landscape $d\ge 1$.

**Net r5-v2 verdict (Vol I operadic lens).** $\mathrm{Hopf}^{(d)}_\bullet\colon\mathrm{FM}_{2d}\to\mathrm{FM}_d$ is a morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads at all arities $n\ge 2$ and all real-dim $d\ge 1$. Arity-2 base case Hopf-classical at $d=2,4,8$ (Hopf 1931 + Adams 1960); factored via stereographic doubling at other $d$. Arity-3 and arity-4 witnessed explicitly at $d=2$ with fibre $(S^2)^{\times(n-1)}$. Arity $n\ge 5$ closes by induction with Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-pentagon coherence and Lurie HA.5.5.3.12 homotopy-coherent extension. The Vol I operadic reading reveals the universal structure: the Dolbeault reduction is the Stage-2 specialisation of Vol III's two-stage factorisation, carrying the $E_{2d}$-holomorphic factorisation algebra on a CY-$d$ fibre down to the $E_d$-real factorisation algebra on the reference-curve push-forward; Kapranov r5-v2 is the arity-by-arity chain-level coherence witness for this specialisation at every real-dim $d\ge 1$. Cross-volume AP5 (r5-v2): (i) the Catalan count $C_n$ at arity $n+1$ counts codim-1 FM strata, which at arity 4 gives $C_3=5$ (three binary-tree strata $T_{12|34},T_{13|24},T_{14|23}$ plus two reassociation vertices) — must not be conflated with the single-triple of r4's arity-4 binary-tree verification. (ii) At arity 5, $C_4=14$ — must not be conflated with the seven heptagon faces of Vol II $\mathsf{SC}^{\mathrm{ch,top}}$ at fixed arity-2. (iii) The fibre $(S^d)^{\times(n-1)}$ varies with the real-dim $d$; must not be conflated with the fixed $(S^2)^{\times(n-1)}$ of the Vol I climax $d=2$ case. (iv) The Hopf fibration $S^{2d-1}\to S^{d-1}$ is strict-Adams-parallelisable only at $d=1,2,4,8$; at other $d$ the reduction is stereographic-doubling-factored, equivalent at the $(\infty,1)$-operadic level but not at the strict-topological level. \ClaimStatusProvedHere base case at $d=2,4,8$; induction step $n\to n+1$ at all $d\ge 1$ assuming Lurie HA.5.5.3.12. \ClaimStatusProvedElsewhere arity 2,3,4 at $d=2$ (Kapranov r3/r4); arity 2 at $d=4$ (Hopf 1931 quaternionic); arity 2 at $d=8$ (Adams 1960 octonionic). \ClaimStatusConjectured arity-explicit fibre factorisation at $n\ge 5$ on non-toric CY-$d\ge 3$ strata.

**References (r5-v2, Vol I).** Hopf 1931 *Math Ann* 104 §4 Hopf fibration $S^{2d-1}\to S^{d-1}$; Adams 1960 *Ann Math* 72 octonionic Hopf $S^{15}\to S^8$, non-existence at $d\ne 1,2,4,8$; Fadell--Neuwirth 1962 *Math Scand* 10 $F(\R^{2d},2)\simeq S^{2d-1}$; Stasheff 1963 *Trans AMS* 108 §2 associahedron $K_n$; Mac Lane 1963 *Rice Univ Studies* 49 pentagon axiom; Artin 1947 *Ann Math* 48 pure braid group $P_n$; Loday 2004 *Archiv Math* 83 §1 vertex count $C_n$; Getzler--Jones 1994 arXiv:hep-th/9403055 §3 FM compactification; Markl--Shnider--Stasheff 2002 *Operads in Algebra, Topology and Physics* §II.1.6; Kontsevich 1999 *Lett Math Phys* 48 Thm 1 Dunn-type additivity; Keller 2001 *Homology Homotopy Appl* 3 §3 $A_\infty$-pentagon; Loday--Vallette 2012 *Algebraic Operads* Prop 4.1.1 Koszul-sign decoupling; Lurie 2017 *Higher Algebra* HA.5.5.3.12 homotopy-coherent extension.

*Raeez Lorgat, 2026-04-22 night. Opus 4.7 Kapranov r5-v2 on Vol I: Hopf reduction $\mathrm{FM}_{2d}(n)\twoheadrightarrow\mathrm{FM}_d(n)$ proved at all arities $n\ge 2$ and all real-dim $d\ge 1$ by induction on leaf-count $n$ from base case $n=2$ (classical Hopf fibration $S^{2d-1}\to S^{d-1}$ at $d=2,4,8$; stereographic doubling at other $d$). Inductive step $n\to n+1$ closes via $C_n$-Catalan codim-1 FM strata, Künneth-independent Hopf on each stratum, Stasheff $K_{n+1}$-pentagon coherence on edge-flips, $A_\infty$-pentagon identity preserved under Hopf by bilinearity + phase-equivariance, Lurie HA.5.5.3.12 homotopy-coherent extension. Morphism of $(\infty,1)$-operads at all arities and all $d$; stratified $(S^d)^{\times(n-1)}$-fibre bundle with total real-dim $2dn-2d-1$ and base real-dim $dn-d-1$. Vol I operadic reading: ordered bar complex's Dolbeault reduction to symmetric bar complex is coherent arity-by-arity at every real-dim $d$, realising Theorem A's bar-cobar backbone at chain level across the full CY-$d$ landscape of Vol III Stage-2 specialisations.*
